[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] # Pull Jira
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ## Overview
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Use this skill to keep a local Jira tracker synchronized with Jira.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Primary outputs:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - Per-ticket markdown notes under `jira/<status_folder>/`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - Root tracker at `jira/INDEX.md` (treat `jira/Index.md` as the same target)
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - Change-focused `## Update` entries per refresh run
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] The user's workflow is: open `jira/INDEX.md` → scan the Top-line View (especially the `Top-line Update` column) → click a ticket key to open the ticket note → scroll to the `Update` section at the bottom for the latest run detail. Do **not** append `#update` (or any `#anchor`) to ticket links in `INDEX.md`: the user's markdown viewer treats `file.md#anchor` as a literal path lookup rather than "open file, jump to anchor," so anchors break the link. Plain `.md` links only.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ## Operating Modes
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ### Mode A: Bulk Status Sync From INDEX (exclude done/resolved)
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Trigger this mode when user asks to refresh all tickets in `jira/INDEX.md`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Read ticket keys from the Top-line View table in `jira/INDEX.md`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Skip rows where status is `Done` or `Resolved` (case-insensitive).
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Pull live Jira `status`, `priority`, `assignee`, `updated`, `changelog`, and `comment` for remaining tickets.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 4. For each ticket:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - If status changed: move note file to new `jira/<status_folder>/`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Update header fields in note file (especially **Status** and **Updated**).
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Append a new run block under `## Update` (see `Update Run Format` below).
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Update `jira/INDEX.md`:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Refresh the single global `**Last Sync:** <timestamp>` line above the table.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Refresh each row's `Top-line Update` cell from the run's Top-line Update sentence.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Recompute the Snapshot counts from actual filesystem folders.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ### Mode B: Pull New Ticket(s)
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Use when the ticket is new (not yet in `jira/INDEX.md`).
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Create the ticket note with these sections:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - `## Scope`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - `## Required Deliverables`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - `## Next Actionable`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - `## Synopsis`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] - `## Update` (seed with the first run block)
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Then add a row to `jira/INDEX.md` and refresh the snapshot counts and Last Sync line.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ### Mode C: Update Existing Ticket(s)
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Use when the ticket already exists locally.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] Append a new run block under `## Update`. Do not rewrite prior runs — keep the run history intact so the user can trace transitions backwards.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] ## Workflow
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Parse input**
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Accept Jira key (`AGI-1234`) or URL.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Deduplicate keys.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Fetch Jira data** — pull at minimum:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - `summary`, `description`, `project`, `issuetype`, `status`, `priority`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - `assignee`, `reporter`, `created`, `updated`, `duedate`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - `labels`, `comment`, `changelog`, `parent`, `subtasks`, `issuelinks`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Map status to folder**
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Normalize: lowercase, spaces → underscore, remove punctuation.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Preferred mappings:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `Ready for Grooming` → `ready_for_grooming`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `In Progress` → `in_progress`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `Ready4Test` → `ready4test`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `Ready for UAT` → `ready_for_uat`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `IN UAT` → `in_uat`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `UAT Failed` → `uat_failed`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `UAT Passed` → `uat_passed`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `Test Failed` → `test_failed`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `Done` / `Resolved` → `resolved`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - If a status is unseen, create `jira/<normalized_status>/` and add it to the Folder Convention list in `INDEX.md`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **Create or refresh note**
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Keep the stable filename if it already exists.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Default filename for a new note: `<KEY>-<slug-summary>.md`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - Required header fields:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - URL, Project, Type, Status, Priority, Assignee, Reporter, Created, Updated, Deadline.
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX] 5. **Required note sections**
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - For a new ticket:
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `## Scope`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `## Required Deliverables`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `## Next Actionable`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `## Synopsis`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]      - `## Update`
[2026-05-06 09:54:11 +0700] [CODEX]    - For an existing ticket:
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX]      - Keep existing sections.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX]      - Append a new run block under `## Update`.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ## Update Run Format (interval-friendly)
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Each refresh run appends a new block under `## Update`. The heading name is exactly `## Update` (not `## Update Log`) — consistent naming lets the user scan across tickets without re-orienting, and keeps `Cmd+F "Update"` reliable inside any single note.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Required structure per run:
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ```markdown
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ### Run: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM (+07)
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] #### Top-line Update
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] <One sentence, under ~150 characters, describing the single most important thing that changed in this run. This sentence is mirrored verbatim into INDEX.md's Top-line Update cell for this ticket.>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] #### What Changed?
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - **Status**: <status transitions since last run, with dates and authors from changelog; or "No change." if unchanged>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - **Technical definition**: <edits to description, AC1…ACn, scope, or in-scope/out-of-scope; quote or summarize the delta; or "No change since <date>.">
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - **Prompt-report request**: <any stakeholder comment asking for a quick/prompt status report, updated metrics, or interim evidence; cite author + date; or "None observed.">
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] #### What Is Next For The Change?
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 1. <Concrete next action grounded in the changes above.>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 2. <Another, if applicable — prefer specificity (file paths, commands, named comments to fetch) over generic verbs.>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Rules:
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - Always emit all three `What Changed?` bullets, even when the value is "No change." or "None observed." — a blank bullet is ambiguous with "I forgot to check."
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - The Top-line Update sentence is the contract between the ticket file and `INDEX.md`. If you would not write this sentence into the Top-line Update cell, you have not written it correctly.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - Do not overwrite prior `### Run:` blocks; append below them in chronological order.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - When the changelog shows a status transition but the rationale is only in comments, say so explicitly and list "fetch comments for <ticket>" as a next action — do not guess the rationale.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ## INDEX.md Format
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Required structure:
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ```markdown
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] # Jira Ticket Index
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ## Folder Convention
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] <bulleted mapping from folder name → Jira status — keep aligned with the preferred mappings above plus any ad-hoc folders that exist on disk>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ## Top-line View
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] **Last Sync:** YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM (+07)
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Clicking a ticket key opens that ticket's note; scroll to the `Update` section at the bottom for the latest run detail.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] | Ticket | Status | Priority | Assignee | Summary | Top-line Update |
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|---|---|---|---|
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] | [KEY](relative/path/to/file.md) | <status> | <priority> | <assignee display name> | <static one-liner describing what the ticket is about> | <latest run's Top-line Update sentence, or "— (baseline YYYY-MM-DD; not re-synced)" if the ticket was not touched in this sync> |
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ## Snapshot (as of YYYY-MM-DD)
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - <one line per non-hidden folder, with the file count>
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] Rules:
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - `**Last Sync:**` is a single global timestamp — it reflects the most recent run of this skill, not per-ticket sync time. Per-ticket sync time lives in each note's `Updated:` header field.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - The `Ticket` column's link is a plain `.md` path — never append `#update` or any other anchor fragment. The user's viewer treats `file.md#anchor` as a literal path and reports file-not-found.
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - The `Summary` column holds the ticket's static nature (it changes only if the Jira summary changes).
[2026-05-06 09:54:12 +0700] [CODEX] - The `Top-line Update` column holds the most recent run's Top-line Update sentence, verbatim. For tickets not touched in this sync, emit `— (baseline YYYY-MM-DD; not re-synced)` so the user can distinguish "nothing changed" from "we did not check."
