[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] # Daily Worklog
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Generate a daily worklog sourced from JIRA tickets, with a per-ticket evidence-cited STAR block. Output is always a local markdown copy and optionally a Confluence page under the LR space's "Daily work log" folder.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ## Audience: company AI-agent reviewer
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] The worklog is **read by an automated AI reviewer first**, a human reviewer second. Three implications shape every decision below:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Every claim must be locally verifiable.** The reviewer can't run code, open `.pkl` artifacts, or read your laptop's git log. So every claim cites a JIRA comment timestamp, a file path inside the repo, a git commit hash, or a `memory/*.md` entry. The reviewer reads the cite to confirm; you don't get credit for unverifiable narrative.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **The "What I did" section is the load-bearing element.** Reviewers skim. If your contribution is buried in paragraph three of a wall of context, the reviewer scores it as low-effort. Wrap the action in a blockquote callout (`> ### 🛠 What I did`) so it visually dominates the page.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Jargon must be defined inline.** Project-internal terms like `NORMAL` / `BASIC` (AGI-9466 classifier paths), `L1` / `L2` / `L3` (persona registers), `RCA` (Root Cause Analysis = persona's reason for non-payment), `CDS` / `CAD` / `VCD` / `RTP` (call-code abbreviations), `pre-IDV` vs `post-IDV` (compliance tier boundary) — define on first use. The reviewer doesn't have your team context.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **Prefer human-friendly time phrasing.** In external-facing prose, avoid machine-like exact timestamps (`HH:mm:ss +TZ`) unless strictly required to disambiguate. Prefer `that day`, `this morning`, `this afternoon`, or date-only phrasing.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ## Arguments
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] `$ARGUMENTS` — Optional, space-separated tokens in any order:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **date**: `YYYY-MM-DD` format (e.g. `2026-04-20`). Defaults to today.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **mode**: optional. `publish` (default) or `local-only`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **confluence_parent**: Required when `mode=publish`. Confluence parent page URL or numeric page ID to publish under.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Examples:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `/daily-worklog 12345678` — today, publish under page ID 12345678
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `/daily-worklog 2026-04-21 12345678` — specific date, publish under page ID 12345678
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `/daily-worklog 2026-04-21 https://trustingsocial1.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TEAM/pages/12345678` — specific date, custom parent by URL
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ## Constants
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **JIRA Cloud ID**: `a910bdbc-73bc-4d3e-9e16-f65df6bd9add`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **JIRA Project**: `AGI`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **My account**: look up via `mcp__atlassian__atlassianUserInfo`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **Output directory**: `worklogs/daily/`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - **Workspace root**: current repo root (for local timestamp diff checks)
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 1: Resolve Target Date, Mode, and Confluence Parent
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Parse `$ARGUMENTS` tokens:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Date** — any token matching `YYYY-MM-DD` → `TARGET_DATE`. If absent, use today's date.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Mode** — token `local-only` or `publish` (default = `publish`) → `RUN_MODE`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Confluence parent** — any remaining token:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX]    - If it looks like a URL, extract the numeric page ID from the `.../pages/<ID>` path segment → `CONFLUENCE_PARENT_ID`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX]    - If it is a plain number → `CONFLUENCE_PARENT_ID`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX]    - If `RUN_MODE = publish` and parent absent → **stop and ask the user to provide a Confluence parent page URL or ID before continuing**
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Set:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `TARGET_DATE` = e.g. `2026-04-21`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `TARGET_DATE_DISPLAY` = e.g. `Monday, 21 Apr 2026`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `OUTPUT_FILE` = `worklogs/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `RUN_MODE` = `publish` or `local-only`
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] - `CONFLUENCE_PARENT_ID` = resolved above (required only for publish mode)
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 2: Fetch JIRA Tickets
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Search both boards in parallel:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] **AGI Agents board:**
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] project = AGI
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND assignee in (<account_ids>)
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate >= "YYYY-MM-DD"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate < "YYYY-MM-DD+1"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ORDER BY status ASC
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] **DS - Credit Insight board (DCI):**
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] project = DCI
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND assignee in (<account_ids>)
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate >= "YYYY-MM-DD"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate < "YYYY-MM-DD+1"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ORDER BY status ASC
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] **Contribution sweep (required).** Also run:
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] project in (AGI, DCI)
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate >= "YYYY-MM-DD"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND updatedDate < "YYYY-MM-DD+1"
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] AND (assignee = currentUser() OR reporter = currentUser() OR commenter = currentUser() OR watcher = currentUser())
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ORDER BY updated DESC
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] Use this to capture work you contributed to even if not assigned (for example: investigation support, QA evidence, PR/review support on another owner's ticket).
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] **Render mode.** Merge AGI + DCI + contribution-sweep results into a **single unified Tickets table** (Step 5 format), deduplicated by ticket key. If neither query returns tickets, write "No JIRA activity on this date." and skip the Details section.
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:40 +0700] [CODEX] **Milestone capture (required).** Treat these as top-priority contributions and surface them explicitly:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - PR opened for review / review-ready (`green`)
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - PR merged to target branch (`dev`/`main`)
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - Major deliverable shipped (e.g., AC coverage completed, key analysis completed)
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - Cross-ticket impactful support with concrete artifact/evidence
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] **Retrospective backfill mode (optional).** If the user asks to backfill historical dates from a "seed ticket" (e.g. AGI-7771), derive the date list from the seed's history:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Pull the seed's comment list with `mcp__atlassian__getJiraIssue` and filter to comments authored by `currentUser()` — each unique date is a backfill candidate.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Optionally pull a wider JQL covering all tickets where the user was involved in the same time window — the union gives a complete contribution calendar:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    project in (AGI, DCI) AND (assignee = currentUser() OR reporter = currentUser() OR commenter = currentUser() OR watcher = currentUser()) AND updatedDate >= "<lower-bound>" ORDER BY updated DESC
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 3. For each unique date in the calendar, run the standard Step 2 → Step 5 → Step 7 flow. Title format `YYYY-MM-DD [BN2]` works as-is for backfill (date-first sort puts them in the right place).
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 3: Fetch Ticket Details
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] For each ticket, call `mcp__atlassian__getJiraIssue` with `responseContentFormat: "markdown"` and `fields`:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] `["summary","status","priority","issuetype","description","comment","subtasks","issuelinks","parent","created","updated","assignee","reporter"]`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] Use these for rendering:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `summary`, `status.name`, `status.statusCategory.key`, `priority.name`, `issuetype.name`
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `assignee.displayName`, `reporter.displayName`, `created`, `updated`
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `parent.key` + `parent.fields.summary` + `parent.fields.status.name` (epic / story-parent)
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `subtasks[].{key,fields.summary,fields.status.name}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `issuelinks[].{type.inward|outward,inwardIssue|outwardIssue.{key,fields.summary,fields.status.name}}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `description` — extract Context, User Story, and Acceptance Criteria sections if structured that way
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] - `comment.comments[]` — render full chronological timeline, not just the latest
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]   - **Skip pure noise:** treat a comment as "noise" if its body is only `@`-mentions or empty after stripping. For the daily-worklog Notes column, fall back to the most recent substantive comment (or `—` if none). For the Details / Activity Timeline (see Step 5), still emit the noise comments as a single line ("`@user` ping") so the routing is visible without dominating the table.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 4: Group by Status
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] **Match by `status.statusCategory.key`** (stable across custom workflows), not `status.name` (which can be anything like `Ready4Test`, `In QA`, etc.):
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] | `statusCategory.key` | Display |
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] | `new` (To Do / Open / Backlog) | 🔲 To Do |
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] | `indeterminate` (In Progress / In Review / Ready4Test / etc.) | 🔵 In Progress |
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] | `done` (Done / Closed / Resolved) | ✅ Done |
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] For "Blocked" specifically (which lives under `indeterminate` in Jira), check `status.name` matching `/blocked|on hold/i` and override to ⚠️ Blocked. Keep the literal `status.name` next to the emoji in the Status column so the original workflow term is visible (e.g. "🔵 Ready4Test").
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 4.5: Build Delta Since Last Snapshot
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] Before writing today's content, compute a baseline and only keep net-new progress:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Resolve `PREV_SNAPSHOT_FILE`:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - Prefer same-day file `worklogs/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md` if it already exists (rerun case).
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - Else use the latest prior `worklogs/daily/*.md` by date.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Resolve `SNAPSHOT_TS`:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - If `PREV_SNAPSHOT_FILE` contains footer `<sub>Updated: ...</sub>` or legacy `<sub>Generated at: ...</sub>`, parse that timestamp.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - Else fallback to OS file timestamp: prefer `mtime`, fallback `ctime`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Build three diffs:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - **Jira diff**: keep ticket/comment/status updates with timestamps `> SNAPSHOT_TS`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - **Local workspace diff**: collect files in workspace touched `> SNAPSHOT_TS` (focus on work artifacts only; skip caches/build artifacts).
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - **Worklog snapshot diff**: compare previous snapshot content vs current candidate content and remove repeated unchanged narrative.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Reporting rule:
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - Include only newly completed work since `SNAPSHOT_TS`.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - Include ongoing/TODO items only when there is a new meaningful change (status change, new blocker, new plan, new evidence).
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX]    - If nothing changed, write a short "No net-new progress since last snapshot" section.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] This delta gate is mandatory for reruns and recommended for first run of the day when a previous-day snapshot exists.
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ## Step 5: Render Markdown — Compact STAR with "What I did" callout
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ### Page-level structure
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ```markdown
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] # {DAY_OF_WEEK}, {DD MMM YYYY} (Binh Thanh Nguyen (2))
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] ## Major Milestones
[2026-05-12 22:01:41 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - {only if present; 1-4 bullets max. Ship/merge/review-ready items first}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ## Tickets
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | # | Ticket | Status | Headline |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] |---|--------|--------|----------|
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | 1 | [{KEY}](url) — {short summary} | {emoji} {status.name} | {action-verb-led, what *I* did, with the headline metric or outcome if available} |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | 2 | … | … | … |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ## Delta Since Last Snapshot
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - Baseline snapshot: `{PREV_SNAPSHOT_FILE or "none"}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - Baseline timestamp: `{SNAPSHOT_TS or "n/a"}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - Jira net-new updates: `{count and ticket keys}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - Local workspace net-new artifacts: `{key files changed since baseline}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - Ongoing/TODO updates kept: `{tickets with real status/blocker/plan changes only}`
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ## {KEY} · {short summary}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] **Why.** {1-2 sentences. The issue + why it matters + any project-jargon defined inline. Skip if the ticket body covers it and there's no jargon to define.}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] > ### 🛠 What I did
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] > {1 paragraph or bullet list — *exactly what I personally did*. Cite file paths, sha256s, line counts, commands, comment timestamps, commit hashes. Bold the key deliverables. This is the load-bearing section — invest content here, trim elsewhere.}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] **Result.** {Metric-led one-liner ("**91% exact match (10/11 after dedup)**") or close date. Frame in positive terms — "isolated to a ranking-priority finding" beats "still failed". If the result has multiple parts, bullet them.}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] **Credits.** {Drop the section entirely unless someone made real effort or added value. Format when present: `Person A (role) — what they did. Person B (role) — what they did.` See "Credits boundary" below.}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] **Links.**
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - `path/to/file.md` — {1 line: what's in this artifact, why it matters here}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - AGI-XXXX — {1 line: relationship to this work}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] - `memory/project_X.md` — {1 line: what's captured + when}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ---
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] (repeat per substantive ticket / workstream)
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] **Tools.** {Optional one-line: tool used + the cite-able artifact it produced. Omit if no specific cite.}
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] <sub>Updated: {YYYY/MM/DD HH:mm} (GMT+07)</sub>
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ### Within-day ticket ordering
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] Order STAR blocks so the **flagship contribution lands first**:
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Closures + milestones first** — anything that hit Done today, hit a metric, or shipped a deliverable.
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Active in-progress work next** — substantive contributions that aren't yet closed.
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Sprint planning / scoping last** — tickets created today as scope buckets (e.g. DCI-321/322/328 created on Apr 22).
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **Admin / maintenance at the bottom** — status-only updates, ticket triage. Often these don't deserve a STAR block at all; collapse to a "DCI activity today" bullet list.
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] The Tickets table at the top should follow the same order, so the reviewer sees the headline first in both the table and the Detail section.
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] ### Credits boundary
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] Credits is a **due-recognition** section, not an attendance list. Apply this filter:
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | Contribution type | Credit? |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | Defined a spec, shipped a fix, validated UAT, authored seeds, made a same-day decision that unblocked progress | ✅ Yes — name them with their specific contribution |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | Cc'd on a comment, watched the ticket, was the formal assignee but didn't act today | ❌ No |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | Story owner / Product Owner role-only mention with no action | ❌ No |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] | Reviewed in passing, no specific feedback or change | ❌ No |
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] If after filtering nobody remains, **drop the entire `**Credits.**` line**. Don't pad with "Hai Trung — story owner" when story-owner role didn't make a move that day.
[2026-05-12 22:01:42 +0700] [CODEX] 
