[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:106:- `TODO: consider promoting to memory` — **"label_first vs label_last is a free system-disagreement signal"**. The 4.59% flip rate between fast and final classifier runs gives confidence bands without running a judge. Compliance flips going cross-category 76% of the time is a regulatory-risk signal that no single-run metric would surface.
[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:107:- `TODO: consider promoting to memory` — **YAML version anchoring uses two layers**: `git.commit.sha` (envelope tag, available on every DD log) for code identity, and content-hash of rendered `call_code_descriptions` for YAML behaviour identity. They diverge when a deploy doesn't touch ccd content; the content hash is the load-bearing identity for classifier reruns.
[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:108:- `TODO: consider promoting to memory` — **DD envelope tags carry deployment fingerprints universally**: `git.commit.sha`, `image_id`, `image_name`, `aws_eks_cluster-name`, `host`. Useful even when application-level fields are missing. For any future "what was running" question, parse tags first.
[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:109:- `TODO: consider promoting to memory` — **Fast-vs-final classifier IS double-run pipeline**. Each conv typically has TWO `EndPostCallAnalysis` events (fast classifier + AssemblyAI final). Naive extraction picks the first; canonical for production-of-record is the last. The same applies to `StartPostCallAnalysis.conversation_caching` if input/output pair-matching matters.
[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:110:- `TODO: consider promoting to memory` — **The Datadog `call_direction_detail` field distinguishes human-handled vs AI-handled calls**. Value `human_outbound`/`human_inbound` = human agent ran it; `ai_outbound`/`ai_inbound` or missing = AI bot. ~24% of Kompato prod is human-handled — this is a permanent population, not noise.
[2026-05-12 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] docs/session_recap/20260512_30d-accounting-yaml-tenant-fingerprint.md:111:- `TODO: consider promoting to skill` — **"MECE litmus + dual-label extraction" pattern**: for any pivot table over a DD population, the unique-conv-count must reconcile across all dimensions. Combined with always carrying first+last for events that fire multiple times per conv, this catches dropouts, miscounts, and arbitrary "first-event-wins" bugs in one go. Worth its own skill writeup.
