[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +## PR #544 / AGI-9466 - Affirm Config Cleanup
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Why.** AGI-9466 covers Affirm disposition-code correctness. The May 12 master call-code reference removed `EPE` and `EPD`, so the local evaluation priority list and config cleanup needed a MECE check before those labels stopped being treated as active outcomes.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> ### What I did
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> That evening, I checked the May 12 master reference against the Affirm config and local priority list, wrote the EPE/EPD MECE impact note, updated `input/priority.csv`, and opened draft PR #544 from `paco-epe-epd-remove` against `dev`. The PR currently changes `scripts/en_collin_kompato_affirm/main.yaml` by 12 additions and 9 deletions at commit `0c45fb5`; its visible patch removes a stale SIF description block and hardens successful-payment postprocess handling for PAY/PIF.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Result.** Draft PR #544 is open, one file changed, with CI in progress when checked. It is not merged and not yet marked review-ready.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Links.**
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- [PR #544](https://github.com/tsocial/agi-sm-dsci-configs/pull/544) - draft PR against `dev`, head `paco-epe-epd-remove`, commit `0c45fb5`.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `docs/mece_audit_20260512_removed_epe_epd.md` - MECE risk analysis for removed EPE/EPD labels and fallback policy.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `input/priority.csv` - local active-label priority list updated after the May 12 master reference review.
