[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +## AGI-9466 - Pipeline Migration And Validation
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Why.** AGI-9466 needs repeatable generation, review, and rerun evidence for Affirm action-code acceptance criteria. The previous `vpbPostCall` layout had active code mixed with archived experiments, which made validation harder to reproduce.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> ### What I did
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> That morning, I consolidated the scattered `vpbPostCall` assets into a single `vpbPostCall/` tree, promoted the active quality loop into `src/kompato/debtor/run_quality_loop_agi9466_all.py`, added the AC-DNC seed in `docs/plan/agi9466_ac_seeds.yaml`, and patched `src/kompato/debtor/agi9466_chat_arena.py` so the pipeline works with zero's older runtime. I also committed the migration locally as `9907209` and recorded the command path in `docs/AGI9466_MIGRATION_20260512.md`.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Result.** Two zero-side L1 happy-path validations passed: AC-DNC reached score 5 after retry hints, and AC-001 NNP reached score 5 on the first cautious-skeptic attempt. The active loop is now the 561-line `src/kompato/debtor/run_quality_loop_agi9466_all.py`, alongside the 1,287-line chat arena implementation.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Links.**
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `docs/session_recap/20260512_vpbpostcall-agi9466-migration.md` - migration recap, validation results, commit scope, and remaining blockers.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `docs/AGI9466_MIGRATION_20260512.md` - canonical path map and run command after the consolidation.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `src/kompato/debtor/run_quality_loop_agi9466_all.py` - active AGI-9466 quality-loop runner.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +- `docs/plan/agi9466_ac_seeds.yaml` - acceptance-criteria seed catalog with the new AC-DNC seed.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +---
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +## DCI-333 / DCI-334 - 30-Day Accounting And Source Pool
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Why.** DCI-333 is the all-code evaluation workstream, while DCI-334 is the broader AF postcall improvement container. Both need a reliable source pool before sampling, rerun, or Auto-QC claims can be made.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> ### What I did
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +> Through the afternoon, I rebuilt the 30-day production conversation ledger from the 9.3 GB Datadog-derived event set, carrying first and last classifier labels, tenant, YAML content hash, required rerun inputs, and local-YAML match status. I then generated the four reconciliation pivots, the source-pool ledger, the local-YAML alignment report, and the historical-YAML recovery pass instead of relying on a sampled view.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Result.** The 47,153-conversation master table reconciles across code-by-company, code-by-YAML, tenant-by-YAML, and code-by-rerun-readiness pivots. The report identifies 35,319 strict rerun-ready conversations, 46,631 relaxed rerun-ready conversations, 2,166 first-vs-last classifier flips, and a 10,506-row recoverable non-current CCD cohort after historical YAML pinning.
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +**Links.**
[2026-05-12 22:08:34 +0700] [CODEX] +
