[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +## DCI-333 / DCI-334 - 30-Day Accounting And Source Pool
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +**Why.** DCI-333 is the all-code evaluation workstream, while DCI-334 is the broader AF postcall improvement container. Both need a reliable source pool before sampling, rerun, or Auto-QC claims can be made.
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +> ### What I did
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +> Through the afternoon, I rebuilt the 30-day production conversation ledger from the 9.3 GB Datadog-derived event set, carrying first and last classifier labels, tenant, YAML content hash, required rerun inputs, and local-YAML match status. I then generated the four reconciliation pivots, the source-pool ledger, the local-YAML alignment report, and the historical-YAML recovery pass instead of relying on a sampled view.
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +
[2026-05-12 22:09:01 +0700] [CODEX] +**Result.** The 47,153-conversation master table reconciles across code-by-company, code-by-YAML, tenant-by-YAML, and code-by-rerun-readiness pivots. The report identifies 35,319 strict rerun-ready conversations, 46,631 relaxed rerun-ready conversations, 2,166 first-vs-last classifier flips, and a 10,506-row recoverable non-current CCD cohort after historical YAML pinning.
