[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Within-day ticket ordering
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] Order STAR blocks so the **flagship contribution lands first**:
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Closures + milestones first** — anything that hit Done today, hit a metric, or shipped a deliverable.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Active in-progress work next** — substantive contributions that aren't yet closed.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Sprint planning / scoping last** — tickets created today as scope buckets (e.g. DCI-321/322/328 created on Apr 22).
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **Admin / maintenance at the bottom** — status-only updates, ticket triage. Often these don't deserve a STAR block at all; collapse to a "DCI activity today" bullet list.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] The Tickets table at the top should follow the same order, so the reviewer sees the headline first in both the table and the Detail section.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Credits boundary
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] Credits is a **due-recognition** section, not an attendance list. Apply this filter:
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Contribution type | Credit? |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Defined a spec, shipped a fix, validated UAT, authored seeds, made a same-day decision that unblocked progress | ✅ Yes — name them with their specific contribution |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Cc'd on a comment, watched the ticket, was the formal assignee but didn't act today | ❌ No |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Story owner / Product Owner role-only mention with no action | ❌ No |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Reviewed in passing, no specific feedback or change | ❌ No |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] If after filtering nobody remains, **drop the entire `**Credits.**` line**. Don't pad with "Hai Trung — story owner" when story-owner role didn't make a move that day.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Links section — bulleted with descriptions
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] The reviewer can't open files on your laptop. Every linked artifact gets a **1-line description** explaining what it is and why it's referenced here. Example:
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ```markdown
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] **Links.**
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - `testing/inputs/testset_agi7771_v1.csv` — frozen 17-row golden testset (sha256 `d55a5796`) used by the AGI-7771 backtest.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - `docs/AGI-7771_PIPELINE_A-D.md` — 4-stage pipeline spec (211 lines, producer/consumer per stage).
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - AGI-9466 — sister ticket; reuses the same A/B/C/D harness for 11-AC eval.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - `memory/project_route_a_backtest.md` — Apr 21 capture of the harness pattern + tc_id collision fix.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ```
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] Avoid the dot-separated single-line form (`A · B · C`) — fine for `**Tools.**` (one cite), bad for Links (where each artifact needs a meaning).
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Timestamp style
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Default to human-friendly time language in narrative and delta sections:
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX]   - good: `updated that day`, `updated this morning`, `updated this afternoon`
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX]   - avoid: `updated at 2026-05-06 09:31 +07`
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Keep exact times only when two events on the same day would otherwise be ambiguous.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Footer format is concise and human-readable: `Updated: YYYY/MM/DD HH:mm (GMT+07)`.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Sizing heuristics
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Day shape | Length |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Single ticket, comment-only contribution | One STAR block, ~30-50 lines |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Multi-ticket (3+) substantive work | STAR per substantive ticket, ~30-60 lines each; compact bullet list for low-touch tickets |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Headline engineering output (testset, harness, infrastructure) | One STAR scoped to *the output*, not per ticket; created tickets just sit in the Tickets table |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Closed/Done today | Result section names the close date and the headline metric in **bold** |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] | Heavy multi-workstream day (rare) | STAR per workstream — can run 100-150 lines total; each workstream ~30-50 lines |
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] User feedback ratio (Apr 24 retrospective): "not too short, content and context both matter" — when in doubt, **expand the Why with jargon definitions and the Links with descriptions**, not the What I did. The action block stays tight; the surrounding context can breathe.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ## Confidentiality Guardrail
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Treat local skills/agents/prompts/configs under user home (for example `~/.codex/skills`, local agent internals, private helper prompts) as private local assets.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Do NOT include those paths or internal asset details in Jira comments, PR descriptions, Confluence pages, or other external-facing outputs.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - Exception: disclose only when the ticket/task explicitly requires building, updating, or reviewing a skill/agent asset itself.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] ### Anti-patterns
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Unsourced narrative.** "Claude Code drove the pipeline scaffolding" without a `docs/X.md` or commit cite is filler. Either cite or cut.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Subagent storytelling.** "Subagent 1 dispatched X, Subagent 2 dispatched Y" — unverifiable without transcripts. Replace with concrete cite-able output: "Claude Code drafted `<file>`."
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Speculative milestone alignment.** "Feeds into the broader strategy of X" without a JIRA link or file is filler. Cite or cut.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Generic "Working notes" sections.** STAR + Tools is the structure. If content doesn't fit, it doesn't belong.
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Implicit credit absorption.** "We ran the classifier" hides who did what. Specifics: "Ran `backtest_from_xlsx.py` on the zero server; Lien validated the result."
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Blockquote-then-paragraph collapse.** Always emit a blank line after a `>` blockquote before any bold-prefixed paragraph (Confluence's markdown→storage converter merges them otherwise, breaking visual hierarchy).
[2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] - **Filler Credits.** If everyone listed is admin-role only, the section makes the page look performative. Drop it.
