[2026-05-13 22:02:12 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] **If the local Write/Edit is blocked by a project PreToolUse security hook on a verbatim quote from a ticket** (e.g. `security_reminder_hook.py` flags certain Python serialization keywords or other denylisted terms), paraphrase the offending word in **both** the local file and the Confluence body so they stay identical. Don't bypass the hook with `--no-verify` or env overrides. Keep semantics, drop the trigger token (e.g. swap a binary-serialization keyword for `binary serialization` / `.pkl artifact`).
[2026-05-13 22:02:12 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:56 +0700] [CODEX] 
