[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] ## Summary
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] Today’s work moved the postcall call-code program from ad hoc evaluation toward an auditable Q2 reporting process. The main output was a clear approach for building the next evaluation dataset from governed production evidence while keeping the company-wide report limited to aggregate methodology and decision gates.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] ## Q2 OKR Alignment
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] | OKR | Today’s Progress | Reporting Value |
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|---|
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] | KR1: increase call-code test data size and per-code coverage | Established a source-pool-first selection method before expanding the evaluation set. | Future test-data growth can be explained as sampled from an accounted pool, not manually assembled rows. |
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] | KR2: reduce human-QC burden through Auto-QC | Identified system-disagreement and configuration-drift checks as priority Auto-QC signals. | Auto-QC can focus on measurable risk patterns instead of broad manual review. |
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] ## Approach
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Build a complete source pool before sampling.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Assign every candidate row to a single accounting bucket so the evaluation set is mutually exclusive and collectively exhaustive.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Separate reporting populations:
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX]    - balanced evaluation set for per-code quality;
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX]    - production holdout for production-weighted monitoring;
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX]    - fixture set for deterministic system or postprocess behavior;
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX]    - audit set for ambiguous or internally inconsistent labels.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Require version and configuration alignment before rerun.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Use synthetic or generated conversations only for coverage gaps that production cannot fill.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] ## Data Selection And Alignment
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] The selection gate is now defined before running additional evaluation:
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Start from the accounted production source pool.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Keep only rows with the required rerun inputs for evaluation use.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Confirm the row was produced under a known configuration version.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Prefer rows whose prompt and call-code definitions match the current approved configuration.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Route older or mismatched configuration groups to historical recovery or separate reporting, not the main current-config evaluation set.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] - Route internally inconsistent labels to Auto-QC/audit instead of treating them as high-confidence labels.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] This prevents mixing rows from different classifier versions and makes the future evaluation result easier to defend.
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] ## Sharing Boundary
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:13 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-13 22:01:58 +0700] [CODEX] This company-wide brief shares the approach and aggregate methodology only. Detailed source records and reconstruction materials are not included here; any evidence sharing should follow the approved data-governance channel.
