[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/main_yaml_v1_full/per_conversation/0105_AmFlMacmBSHY49WImD-gYQ/llm_call_0002.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a reviewer agent in the finance and banking sector.\nYou will receive a transcript of a phone call related to debt collection and recovery, located in the section PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT.\nThe transcript includes two participants: the debt collector (assistant) and the customer (user).\nYour task is to analyze this transcript and write a write a short, concise, and simple summary of the call focusing on the customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n\n# PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\nassistant: Hello\nuser: Hello?\nassistant: Hello, I am Sarah, a virtual agent on a recorded line.\nassistant: May I please speak with Cynthia Scottdaies?\nuser: Speaking.\nassistant: Hi Cynthia, to protect your privacy and consent to proceed with the call, could you please confirm your month and day of birth?\nuser: Three nine sixty six.\nassistant: Got it.\nassistant: Just to confirm, did you say your birthdate is March ninth?\nuser: Yeah.\nassistant: Thanks.\nassistant: Again, my name is Sarah - a virtual assistant from Kompato.\nassistant: This is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector.\nassistant: Any information obtained will be used for that purpose.\nassistant: In case we're disconnected, may I call you back at this number?\nuser: Sure. Who's the debt person?\nassistant: Okay  We are contacting you on behalf of Republic Finance regarding your credit card with a balance of four thousand, two hundred and ninety-three dollars and thirty cents.\nassistant: For your convenience, is it okay if we communicate via text?\nuser: Yeah.\nassistant: Thank you.\nuser: I had a heart surgery.\nassistant: Gotcha  I'm sorry to hear about your heart surgery, Cynthia.\nuser: It was\nassistant: I can only imagine how challenging that must have been.\nuser: I'm recovering well, and it was a tough time.\nassistant: I'm glad to hear you're recovering well, Cynthia.\nassistant: It sounds like it was a challenging period for you.\nassistant: How are things looking for you financially now?\nuser: I'm getting back on on track.\nassistant: That's great to hear, Cynthia.\nassistant: Since you're getting back on track, how would you like to resolve this balance?\nassistant: I'm here to help.\nuser: Okay. So I would like to\nuser: like, make payments until I get this down.\nassistant: Okay.\nassistant: We can set up a payment plan for you.\nassistant: How much would you be comfortable paying monthly?\nuser: I would like to do like, a hundred dollars a week.\nassistant: Got it.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: With $100 weekly, that would be around $400 a month.\nassistant: Let me calculate how many weeks it would take to pay off the balance.\nassistant: Would you like me to proceed with that?\nuser: Sure.\nassistant: With a balance of four thousand, two hundred and ninety-three dollars and thirty cents, paying $100 weekly would take approximately 43 weeks to pay off.\nassistant: Does this work for you?\nuser: Sure.\nassistant: Great!\nassistant: Could you let me know a convenient date to start your first $100 payment?\nuser: Hold on one second. I pull up my calendar.\nassistant: Take your time.\nassistant: Let me know when you're ready.\nuser: Okay.\nassistant: Alright, what date works best for your first $100 payment?\nuser: Okay.\nassistant: Could you please confirm the date you'd like to start your first $100 payment?\nuser: The eight April the eighth.\nassistant: The date you provided, April 8th, is in the past.\nuser: No. No. No. No. No.\nassistant: Got it.\nuser: April the twenty fifth.\nassistant: Got it.\nuser: Mhmm.\nassistant: Your first $100 payment will be on April 25th.\nassistant: Just to confirm, you'll be making weekly payments of $100 starting April 25th until the balance is paid off.\nassistant: Is that correct?\nuser: Uh-huh.\nuser: Yes. Yes.\nassistant: Sorry please hold a moment.\nassistant: Perfect.\nassistant: Thank you, Cynthia.\nassistant: Before we wrap up, could you please confirm your contact information?\nassistant: Is your phone number still three two one three one eight eight eight zero zero?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Great, thank you.\nassistant: Currently, you can make your payments online or via mail.\nassistant: Which do you prefer?\nuser: Online.\nassistant: Got it.\nuser: Ready. Oh, wait a minute. Wait a minute.\nuser: Can you repeat that reference number?\nassistant: Sure!\nassistant: The reference number is 1, 1, 0, 2, 3, 8, 5, 8, 3.\nassistant: Let me know if you need me to repeat it again.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Thank you.\nassistant: To ensure important account updates reach you timely, could we take a moment to update your contact details?\nuser: Sure.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: I have cdaies at yahoo dot com as your email address in my records.\nassistant: Is this still accurate?\nuser: Yes. Yes.\nassistant: Thank you for confirming.\nuser: Yes.\nuser: Yes. Yes.\nassistant: I also have six three one three  POWERS POINTE Circle, ORLANDO, Florida, three two eight one eight  as your mailing address in my records.\nassistant: Is this still accurate?\nuser: Mhmm. Yes.\nassistant: gotcha  Thank you for confirming your contact details, Cynthia.\nassistant: If you have any other questions, feel free to reach out to us at our hotline: one two one four one five seven eight six three.\nassistant: Thank you for your time today.\nassistant: We appreciate your cooperation.\nassistant: Have a wonderful day.\nassistant: Goodbye.\n\n# Instructions\n1. Read the transcript carefully.\n2. Identify the key points and outcomes of the call focusing on customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n3. Write a short summary of the call, should ONLY 2-3 sentences\n4. Return the summary wrapped bettween <output> and </output> tags.\n\n# Example output format\n<output>\nYour summary here ...\n</output>"
[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/signal_experiment_40_dtmf_rerun_20260513_1655/per_conversation/0019_2W7wMJTYcntppQ6RHAwbRA/llm_call_0006.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a professional note-taking specialist for debt collection calls. Your task is to analyze the conversation transcript and create a concise, flowing summary note in the style of a live agent for updating the System of Record (SOR).\n\n# Instructions\nExtract and summarize the following 8 categories of information from the call transcript into a single, natural-flowing paragraph:\n\n## 1. Recording Disclosure\n- State whether recording disclosure was given or not given\n- Use phrases like: \"Recording disclosure given\" or \"Recording disclosure not given\"\n\n## 2. Verified First & Last Name\n- Include the consumer's verified full name\n- Use phrases like: \"confirmed speaking to [First Last]\" or \"verified identity of [First Last]\"\n- If name not verified, note: \"unable to verify identity\"\n\n## 3. Verification Method\n- Specify how identity was verified: DOB (date of birth), Last 4 of SSN (social security number)\n- Use phrases like: \"verified by DOB\", \"verified by Last 4 of SSN\"\n- If not verified, note: \"identity not verified\"\n\n## 4. Mini Miranda\n- State whether Mini Miranda was provided by agent/assistant or not\n- Here is the mini miranda statement: \"this is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector. Any information obtained will be used for that purpose.\"\n- Use phrases like: \"gave mini miranda\", \"provided mini miranda\", or \"mini miranda not provided\"\n\n## 6. Call Purpose & Discussion Summary\nThis is the core of the notes. Include:\n- **Balance discussed**: \"Adv balance of $[amount]\" or \"Spoke regarding balance of $[amount]\"\n- **Consumer response**: Their reaction, concerns, or intentions\n- **Payment options discussed**: What options were presented (if any)\n- **Settlement offer(s)**: Any settlement amounts offered and consumer's response\n- **Dispute raised**: If yes, briefly note: \"Dispute raised - [reason]\"\n- **Fraud claim**: If yes, note: \"Fraud claim made - [details]\" and if fraud steps were provided\n\n## 7. Demographic Updates\nInclude any updated contact information:\n- **Phone**: \"updated phone number to [number]\" or \"phone current on file\"\n- **Email**: \"updated email to [email]\" or \"email current on file\"\n- **Address**: \"updated address to [address]\" or \"addy current on file\"\n- If no updates: \"contact info current on file\" or similar\n\n## 8. Consents\n- **Text/email consent**: \"Text/email permission YES\" or \"Text/email permission NO\" or \"Text/email permission N/A\"\n- **Callback consent within 7 days**:\n  - \"Consent to callback within 7 days YES\" if the customer/user agreed to be called back after disconnected\n  - \"Consent to callback within 7 days NO\" if the customer/user refused to be called back\n  - Other cases: \"Consent to callback within 7 days N/A\"\n\n## 9. Call Transfer (if applicable)\n- If call was transferred or callback scheduled, note: \"Transferred to [department]\" or \"Callback scheduled for [specific time/date]\"\n\n# Writing Style Guidelines\n- Write in a concise, professional tone similar to live agent notes\n- Flow information naturally in a paragraph format, not as bullet points\n- Omit categories that are not applicable or where no information was gathered\n- Focus on actionable information relevant for SOR updates\n- Keep the entire note to 3-5 sentences maximum\n\n# PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\n```\nuser: eight eight three nine zero seven nine five is not available.\nuser: eight eight three nine zero seven nine five.\nuser: eight eight three nine zero seven nine five.\nassistant: \nuser: 8-8-3-9-0-7-9-5. Is not available. The mailbox is full and cannot accept any messages at this time. Goodbye.\n```\n\n# Response Format\nReturn ONLY the summary note as plain text without any tags, formatting, or labels. Write it as a single flowing paragraph.\n\n# Examples\n\n## Example 1: Successful Payment Setup\nRecording disclosure given, confirmed speaking to [First Last], verified by DOB, gave mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], consumer stated that they were looking to resolve for a lesser amount. Gave settlement of $[amount] to resolve, consumer agreed, set up payment for [date]. Text/email permission YES, updated phone number to [phone number], email and address are current on file. Consent to callback within 7 days YES.\n\n## Example 2: Dispute Raised\nRecording disclosure given, verified identity of [First Last] by SSN, provided mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], consumer disputed the amount claiming payment was made in [month year] via bank transfer. Dispute raised - claims already paid, provided validation documents will be reviewed. Contact info current on file. Text/email consent YES, no callback consent needed.\n\n## Example 3: Callback Requested\nRecording disclosure not given, spoke with [First Last], unable to verify at this time. Consumer stated not convenient to talk, requested callback tomorrow between [time range]. Did not discuss balance or payment options. Consumer agreed to callback within 7 days. Text consent N/A.\n\n## Example 4: Payment Plan Discussed\nRecording disclosure given, confirmed speaking to [First Last], verified by address, gave mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], discussed payment options. Consumer interested in payment plan, offered [number] monthly payments of $[amount], consumer requested time to consider. Updated email to [email address], phone and address current. Text/email permission YES, consent to callback within 7 days YES.\n\n## Example 5: Wrong Number/Third Party\nRecording disclosure given, party answered stated not the consumer, indicated wrong number. Did not verify identity. Call terminated. No further information collected."
