7:11 UTC call_id: toye1i6UT36UlfnujlSUxQ, call_code: NLM, call_status: success, summary: The call went to the customer's voicemail, where the customer, Amy, stated she was unavailable and would return the call at her earliest convenience. No further interaction or outcome occurred during the call., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .\", 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS@yahoo.com with message_id 736839.', '2025-11-28 15:42:45 UTC call_id: 7aFylhgBWuFTXhjo1Xbw-g, call_code: NLM, call_status: success, summary: The call was unanswered as the customer, Amy, was unavailable and provided a voicemail indicating she would return the call at her earliest convenience. The virtual agent, Chris, left a message with contact details and information about live and virtual agent availability for assistance., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS@yahoo.com with message_id 687459.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS@yahoo.com with message_id 670170.', '2025-11-25 20:21:42 UTC call_id: nziACgPzSXnU556cRwSf5A, call_code: NLM, call_status: success, summary: The call was a voicemail from a Kompato AI debt collection virtual agent attempting to contact the customer, Amy. The agent provided callback information, including a phone number and availability schedule for both live and virtual agents. No response or action was taken by the customer during this call., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 619399.', '2025-11-21 21:48:42 UTC call_id: 8gkUjMT-MJfzY3K5UrX-jA, call_code: NLM, call_status: success, summary: The customer, Amy, was unavailable to take the call and expressed intent to return the call at her earliest convenience. No specific details or outcomes were discussed during this interaction., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id bf31ee5b-cbf1-4d07-9369-896edcce9056.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 67f01738-1c84-4a5e-bd82-3ee2d5b45a1e.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 57d2e4e1-8cc4-4b30-96aa-15afd5eb69be.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 16132b69-9de4-47f9-ac45-ceadd1a36558.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS@gmail.com with message_id ef067ef2-817f-425c-976f-175cc63a1b3d.', \"2025-10-23 01:01:38 UTC call_id: B2FizGZA3I7xsMIypoyb6Q, call_code: HUP, call_status: success, summary: The call did not progress as the customer remained silent for an extended period and did not respond to the debt collector's greeting. No intent or outcomes were identified due to the lack of engagement from the customer., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .\", 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 0bb8f287-e6a5-4965-b2b2-9ca73fb27e93.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 4ab03e6e-81be-4ab3-8cf5-f5a7ecc0030c.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id 2e0cb875-2229-4d5b-bb78-efa6b2a40e53.', 'Email sent via SENDGRID to AMYGFWILLIAMS3@gmail.com with message_id fa395c05-faae-430c-803b-bda05b36789a.', '2025-10-07 16:05:13 UTC call_id: 2HJoxlvtC5Zqy3B1ITrMXg, call_code: HUP, call_status: success, summary: The customer mentioned \"Legacies\" but did not provide further details or clarify their intent. The assistant sought clarification and encouraged the customer to share more but did not receive a response. The call concluded without any meaningful engagement or resolution., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .', '2025-09-23 18:54:05 UTC call_id: KebA8QS307a8eJvT-4GX3Q, call_code: NLM, call_status: success, summary: The call was made by a virtual agent from Kompato AI to Amy, but it reached her voicemail. The agent left a message providing contact details and availability for both live and virtual agents to assist further., summary_complaints: , summary_situation: , summary_verification: .']\n\n## Expected Input Format\n\nYou are provided with the entire conversation between the collector and the debtor. Each line has the following format: `[timestamp (optinal)] [role]: [line]`, where:\n- `timestamp` represents the time the message occurs and is optional.\n- `role` indicates whom is speaking, and can take only two values, 'user' for the debtor/customer/consumer, and 'assistant' for the bank agent/collector.\n- `line` is the message spoken by the debtor or the bank agent (depending on the role).\n\n\n## Expected Output Format\n\nReturn the output in list of mutiple dict, where each item is the answer to one question. Each item MUST contain these keys:\n- `code`: The question code (e.g., \"POLICY-ADHERENCE_Debt-Mention\"), as provided in the questionaire\n- `reasoning`: Return `No issue` if the assistant satisfied the question. If the assistant made a mistake and failed the task, explain why in details. If the condition for the behavior never occurred, make a note of that.\n- `evidence`: Return the excerpt of the turn (or turns) in the conversation (with their timestamp if exist in conversation script) where the assistant satisfied or failed the question. If there is no exact excerpt, provide a summary or insights found from the conversation. If no evidence is present in the conversation, return `No evidence found`. Make it short.\n- `evidence_cat`: \n  - `strong`: if the evidence is shown clearly in the conversation via exact keyword or direct quote.\n  - `weak`: if it is partially present or can be implied in the conversation, or uncertainty\n  - `not_found`: if no evidence is found in the transcript\n- `answer`: Provide an answer to a question by responding with only \"yes\", \"no\", or \"na\", followed by the possible answers to that question itself. Do not give any explanation here.\n  - `yes`: The required behavior was fully observed.\n  - `no`: The required behavior was contradicted.\n  - `na`: The requirement of the question did not become relevant during the call, meaning the agent was not expected to perform that action based on the call's events.\n\n\n**IMPORTANT**: You MUST return as many items in your output as the number of questions provided in the questionnaire.\n\nThe output must be in this JSON format, for example:\n\n[\n  {{\n    \"code\": \"POLICY-ADHERENCE_Identify-Name-Ask\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The assistant asked to speak with the intended customer using the name on record.\",\n    \"evidence\": \"[2025-11-10T20:14:15Z] assistant: Am I speaking with Jennifer Galloway?\",\n    \"evidence_cat\": \"strong\",\n    \"answer\": \"yes\"\n  }},\n  {{\n    \"code\": \"DISCLOSURE_RPC-Fail-Or-Not-Complete\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The customer has a third-party handling their debt.\",\n    \"evidence\": \"When the assistant informed the customer about their debt, the customer said 'Someone has been taking care of it for me' then hang up without clarifying if the third-party was an attorney or a debt settlement company.\",\n    \"evidence_cat\": \"weak\",\n    \"answer\": \"yes\",\n  }},\n  {{\n    \"code\": \"POLICY-ADHERENCE_Identify-DOB-Ask\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The customer said `Sorry, maybe not.`, which is not explicitly denied.\",\n    \"evidence\": \"[2025-11-12T10:22:08Z] assistant: Thank you for confirming. To protect your privacy, could you please provide your day and month of birth?\\n[2025-11-12T10:23:01Z] user: Sorry, maybe not.\",\n    \"evidence_cat\": \"weak\",\n    \"answer\": \"no\",\n  }},\n  {{\n    \"code\": \"POLICY-ADHERENCE_Voicemail-Detection\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"No voicemail detected in this conversation.\",\n    \"evidence\": \"The customer confirmed their identity, and the assistant proceeded with processing the debt flow.\",\n    \"evidence_cat\": \"not_found\",\n    \"answer\": \"na\",\n  }},\n  {{\n    \"code\": \"DISCLOSURE_Mini-Miranda-Before-Debt-Discussion\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The mini-Miranda disclosure was delivered before any specific debt details were mentioned.\",\n    \"evidence\": \"[2025-11-05T04:31:02Z] assistant: I must advise that this is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector. Any information obtained will be used for that purpose.\\n[2025-11-05T05:31:02Z] assistant: I'm calling about your account with Tennessee Title Loans Inc. , with a balance of two hundred and ninety-four dollars.\",\n    \"evidence_cat\": \"strong\",\n    \"answer\": \"yes\",\n  }},\n  ...\n]\n\n\n## Questions\n\n- HALLUCINATION_01:\n        + During call, Return 'na' if the agent/AI did not make any factual claim about amount, payoff, settlement, eligibility, dates, comms history, legal, credit reporting, SOL (not include claim related to user's identity (name, dob, ssn, zipcode), Mini-Miranda disclosure).\n          Otherwise, if the collector (assistant) has mentioned any of these aspects (not include claim related to user's identity (name, dob, ssn, zipcode), Mini-Miranda disclosure), verify whether a corresponding field exists and matches in the System of Record (SoR).\n          For the payment offer amount from the agent:\n            - It's only need to complie with the conditions from Payment Terms & Offers. \n            - When evaluating payment plans, consider whether the total proposed payments align with the stated balance, allowing for flexibility in the final installment if specified or implied.\n          Return:\n            - if all checks are correct, return 'yes'\n            - if at least one check is incorrect, return 'no'\n          \n        + possible answers: yes | no | na\n- HALLUCINATION_02:\n        + During call, Did the AI/Agent limit its statements to outcomes within its control, avoiding promises such as credit score improvement or lawsuit prevention? Return:\n            - when outcome claim references uncontrollable results, return 'no', for examples: \n              -- \"This will remove the debt from your credit report.\"\n              -- OR, \"Paying today will improve your credit score.\"\n              -- OR, \"We'll stop all legal action immediately.\"\n              -- OR, \"We'll send your payment confirmation today.\"\n            - otherwise, return 'yes'\n        + possible answers: yes | no\n- HALLUCINATION_03:\n        + During call, Did the AI/Agent provide consistent information throughout the conversation (e.g., the same balance each time it was quoted)?\n            Note: The agent can provide various payment plans as long as they meet the conditions outlined in the Payment Terms & Offers. Return:\n            - no: when two or more claims of same type conflict without correction\n            - yes: otherwise\n        + possible answers: yes | no\n- HALLUCINATION_04:\n        + During call, Did the AI/Agent refrain from referring to consumer rights, legal action, or credit reporting without evidence of legal basis?\n          Legal references include (but are not limited to):\n            - Litigation or legal action: lawsuit, court, legal department, judgment, attorney, subpoena, settlement.\n            - Credit reporting: credit bureau, credit file, tradeline, Equifax, Experian, TransUnion, report/delete from credit.\n            - Consumer rights or regulations: rights, dispute, validation letter, FDCPA, FCRA, CFPB, consumer protection.\n            - Enforcement or government references: police, sheriff, arrest, garnishment, investigation, regulator, law enforcement.\n            - Regulatory citations or pseudo-legal language: \"under the law\", \"by law\", \"legally required\", \"federal regulation\", \"section 809\", \"U.S.C.\", \"Regulation E\".\n          \n          Return:\n          - if the agent did NOT use any of the language above, return 'yes'\n          - if the agent DID use any language above, return 'no', e.g. \"We'll file a lawsuit tomorrow\", \"We've reported this to the credit bureau.\"\n        + possible answers: yes | no\n\n## Input\n\nThe conversation to be assessed for compliance is the following:\n```\nuser: You have reached Amy. I'm not in at the moment. I'm sorry I missed your call. I will call you back at my earliest convenience. Have a blessed day. Bye.\nassistant: \n```\n"
