[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/signal_experiment_40_dtmf_rerun_20260513_1655/per_conversation/0023_PmVT8hG7m4pkn5UHlG65jg/llm_call_0010.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a professional note-taking specialist for debt collection calls. Your task is to analyze the conversation transcript and create a concise, flowing summary note in the style of a live agent for updating the System of Record (SOR).\n\n# Instructions\nExtract and summarize the following 8 categories of information from the call transcript into a single, natural-flowing paragraph:\n\n## 1. Recording Disclosure\n- State whether recording disclosure was given or not given\n- Use phrases like: \"Recording disclosure given\" or \"Recording disclosure not given\"\n\n## 2. Verified First & Last Name\n- Include the consumer's verified full name\n- Use phrases like: \"confirmed speaking to [First Last]\" or \"verified identity of [First Last]\"\n- If name not verified, note: \"unable to verify identity\"\n\n## 3. Verification Method\n- Specify how identity was verified: DOB (date of birth), Last 4 of SSN (social security number)\n- Use phrases like: \"verified by DOB\", \"verified by Last 4 of SSN\"\n- If not verified, note: \"identity not verified\"\n\n## 4. Mini Miranda\n- State whether Mini Miranda was provided by agent/assistant or not\n- Here is the mini miranda statement: \"this is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector. Any information obtained will be used for that purpose.\"\n- Use phrases like: \"gave mini miranda\", \"provided mini miranda\", or \"mini miranda not provided\"\n\n## 6. Call Purpose & Discussion Summary\nThis is the core of the notes. Include:\n- **Balance discussed**: \"Adv balance of $[amount]\" or \"Spoke regarding balance of $[amount]\"\n- **Consumer response**: Their reaction, concerns, or intentions\n- **Payment options discussed**: What options were presented (if any)\n- **Settlement offer(s)**: Any settlement amounts offered and consumer's response\n- **Dispute raised**: If yes, briefly note: \"Dispute raised - [reason]\"\n- **Fraud claim**: If yes, note: \"Fraud claim made - [details]\" and if fraud steps were provided\n\n## 7. Demographic Updates\nInclude any updated contact information:\n- **Phone**: \"updated phone number to [number]\" or \"phone current on file\"\n- **Email**: \"updated email to [email]\" or \"email current on file\"\n- **Address**: \"updated address to [address]\" or \"addy current on file\"\n- If no updates: \"contact info current on file\" or similar\n\n## 8. Consents\n- **Text/email consent**: \"Text/email permission YES\" or \"Text/email permission NO\" or \"Text/email permission N/A\"\n- **Callback consent within 7 days**:\n  - \"Consent to callback within 7 days YES\" if the customer/user agreed to be called back after disconnected\n  - \"Consent to callback within 7 days NO\" if the customer/user refused to be called back\n  - Other cases: \"Consent to callback within 7 days N/A\"\n\n## 9. Call Transfer (if applicable)\n- If call was transferred or callback scheduled, note: \"Transferred to [department]\" or \"Callback scheduled for [specific time/date]\"\n\n# Writing Style Guidelines\n- Write in a concise, professional tone similar to live agent notes\n- Flow information naturally in a paragraph format, not as bullet points\n- Omit categories that are not applicable or where no information was gathered\n- Focus on actionable information relevant for SOR updates\n- Keep the entire note to 3-5 sentences maximum\n\n# PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\n```\nuser: Hello?\nassistant: [happy] Hey, this is Emily, a virtual agent on a recorded line.\nuser: Hello?\nassistant: Is this Teresa Leroy?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: [confident] To protect your privacy and proceed with the call, I have June 10, 1957 as your birthdate on file. Is that correct?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Thank you for confirming. I'm calling from Kompato on behalf of Bureaus Investment Group Portfolio Number 15 LLC. [supportive] I must advise that this is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector. Any information obtained will be used for that purpose. [supportive] Teresa, I'm calling about your account with Capital One, National Association, with a balance of seven hundred and thirty-nine dollars and seventeen cents. Could you please tell me about the circumstances that led to the default?\nuser: Yes. Um, I can't work right now.\nassistant: [compassionate] I'm sorry to hear that, Teresa. That must be a challenging situation for you. To help me find the best-\nuser: It is.\nassistant: [understanding] I can imagine how difficult this must be for you. [supportive] Your account balance is seven hundred and thirty-nine dollars and seventeen cents. To assist you, we can settle the total balance to five hundred and eighteen dollars, saving you two hundred and twenty-two dollars. This would reduce your monthly payment to eighty-seven dollars for six months, with the last installment being eighty-three dollars. Would this adjusted amount be manageable for you?\nuser: No.\nassistant: [understanding] I see. -\nuser: two i.\nassistant: [confused] I'm sorry, could you clarify what you mean by \"two i\"?\nuser: Too high. I won't be able to pay for my medicine.\nassistant: [compassionate] I understand, Teresa. Your health is a priority, and I want to help find a solution that works for you. [supportive] We can explore a lower settlement option. We could settle your account for four hundred and forty-four dollars, which reduces your monthly payment to seventy-four dollars for six months. Would this be more manageable for you?\nuser: No.\nassistant: -\nuser: No. Fifty.\nassistant: [supportive] I understand you're suggesting fifty dollars. The minimum monthly amount for the settlement offer is seventy-four dollars. [encouraging] Would it be possible to adjust slightly closer to that amount?\nuser: It'd be hard.\nassistant: [understanding] I see how that could be difficult. [supportive] If seventy-four dollars isn't feasible, we can schedule a keep-in-touch arrangement for three months with a minimum monthly amount of fifty dollars. Would that work better for you?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: [supportive] Great. Could you let me know a convenient date within the next 30 days to start the first payment of fifty dollars?\nuser: The twenty seventh.\nassistant: [supportive] Just to confirm, you'll be making a monthly payment of fifty dollars starting on May 27, 2026. Is that correct?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Please note that nothing we discuss overshadows your rights as expressed in our email to you. For any reason we get disconnected, do we have permission to call you back?\nuser: Yes.\nuser: I have no email anyway.\nassistant: [professional] Thank you for confirming. Since you mentioned you don't have an email, we can send any necessary information via text. Which payment method are you planning to use\u2014debit card, credit card, or-\nuser: Money order.\nassistant: Understood-\nuser: Money order. I have bank account.\nassistant: [professional] Thank you for sharing that. If you're planning to send a money order, you can mail it to our address at three seven one zero  Rawlins Street, Suite one four two zero , Dallas, Texas seven five two one nine . [supportive] We also have an online payment portal at kompatoai. com for your convenience. [supportive] Now, let's ensure we have your most up-to-date contact information. I have CHRISLEROY two one zero nine at GMAIL dot COM as your email address in my records. Is this still accurate?\nuser: I don't have an email address.\nassistant: [supportive] Thank you for letting me know. I'd appreciate it if you could provide me with a new email address to reach you. May I have the best email to contact you?\nuser: I don't have one.\nassistant: [understanding] That's okay. We'll proceed without an email address for now. [supportive] I also have nine three zero  E 1st Street Unit two three , Long Beach, California, nine zero eight zero two as your mailing address in my records. Is this still accurate?\nuser: Yes.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: [appreciative] Thank you for confirming. [supportive] Lastly, I have five six two six six one zero zero five one as your contact number. Is this still the best way to reach you?\nuser: Yes.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: [appreciative] Thank you for confirming all your contact details. [supportive] If you have any further questions or need assistance, feel free to reach out. Have a good day!\nuser: <SILENCE_5s>\nassistant: \n```\n\n# Response Format\nReturn ONLY the summary note as plain text without any tags, formatting, or labels. Write it as a single flowing paragraph.\n\n# Examples\n\n## Example 1: Successful Payment Setup\nRecording disclosure given, confirmed speaking to [First Last], verified by DOB, gave mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], consumer stated that they were looking to resolve for a lesser amount. Gave settlement of $[amount] to resolve, consumer agreed, set up payment for [date]. Text/email permission YES, updated phone number to [phone number], email and address are current on file. Consent to callback within 7 days YES.\n\n## Example 2: Dispute Raised\nRecording disclosure given, verified identity of [First Last] by SSN, provided mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], consumer disputed the amount claiming payment was made in [month year] via bank transfer. Dispute raised - claims already paid, provided validation documents will be reviewed. Contact info current on file. Text/email consent YES, no callback consent needed.\n\n## Example 3: Callback Requested\nRecording disclosure not given, spoke with [First Last], unable to verify at this time. Consumer stated not convenient to talk, requested callback tomorrow between [time range]. Did not discuss balance or payment options. Consumer agreed to callback within 7 days. Text consent N/A.\n\n## Example 4: Payment Plan Discussed\nRecording disclosure given, confirmed speaking to [First Last], verified by address, gave mini miranda. Advised balance of $[amount], discussed payment options. Consumer interested in payment plan, offered [number] monthly payments of $[amount], consumer requested time to consider. Updated email to [email address], phone and address current. Text/email permission YES, consent to callback within 7 days YES.\n\n## Example 5: Wrong Number/Third Party\nRecording disclosure given, party answered stated not the consumer, indicated wrong number. Did not verify identity. Call terminated. No further information collected."
[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/main_yaml_v1_full/per_conversation/0005_WIAOSgwYewHhRpNOUX4lXw/llm_call_0002.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a reviewer agent in the finance and banking sector.\nYou will receive a transcript of a phone call related to debt collection and recovery, located in the section PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT.\nThe transcript includes two participants: the debt collector (assistant) and the customer (user).\nYour task is to analyze this transcript and write a write a short, concise, and simple summary of the call focusing on the customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n\n# PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\nuser: You have reached Amy. I'm not in at the moment. I'm sorry I missed your call. I will call you back at my earliest convenience. Have a blessed day. Bye.\nassistant: \n\n# Instructions\n1. Read the transcript carefully.\n2. Identify the key points and outcomes of the call focusing on customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n3. Write a short summary of the call, should ONLY 2-3 sentences\n4. Return the summary wrapped bettween <output> and </output> tags.\n\n# Example output format\n<output>\nYour summary here ...\n</output>"
[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/signal_experiment_40_dtmf_rerun_20260513_1655/per_conversation/0006_DWdQ_XF6hNSl0FLbjj8ESA/llm_call_0005.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a reviewer agent in the finance and banking sector.\nYou will receive a transcript of a phone call related to debt collection and recovery, located in the section PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT.\nThe transcript records the conversation of 2 roles: the debt collector (assistant/agent) and the customer (user/customer).\n\nYour task is to analyze this transcript and extract any NEW contact information that the customer/user provides about themselves during the call.\n\n## CRITICAL Guidelines - What to Extract\n1. **ONLY extract contact information when:**\n  - The customer/user provides their OWN personal contact information\n  - Customer says \"my new number\", \"you can reach me at\", \"I moved to\"\n  - Information is explicitly about the customer's personal contact details\n\n2. **DO NOT extract:**\n  - Contact info for relatives, attorneys, DSC/CCCS companies, or employers\n  - Information the assistant/agent provides about their own company (the debt collector)\n  - When user asks \"what's your address?\" and assistant answers \u2192 This is NOT customer contact info\n  - Any contact info where assistant/agent says \"our\", \"my\", \"we\", \"the company\"\n\n3. **Additional rules:**\n  - Extract contact info as-is from the transcript without normalization\n  - If customer provides multiple values for the same field, extract the most recent one\n  - If customer updates or corrects previously stated info, extract the corrected version\n  - Ignore confirmations of existing contact info unless explicitly stated as \"new\" or \"updated\"\n\n## Assistant/Agent Company contact info:\n```\n- Company name: null\n- Company mailing address: null\n- Company phone: null\n- Company email: null\n```\nNote: The above information represents the debt collector/agent company. If any fields show \"Not provided\" or are empty, ignore them. Do NOT extract this as the customer's contact information.\n\n## PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\n```\nassistant: Hi, this is Reason Dixon speaking on a recorded line here at Kompato AI. How may I assist you today?\nuser: I'm here. So this is Connie Parrish. They had me, um, to set up a payment for $150 one week, $150 the next week, through credit\u2014 I mean, through Citric Bank. Is this the right person I'm talking to?\nassistant: Uh, you said for Citric Bank? Wait,\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: hold on.\nuser: Hi.\nassistant: Just to confirm we have the right party on the line, I show a date of birth of December 28th,\nuser: That's great.\nassistant: 1965. Is that correct?\nuser: That's\nassistant: Thank you. Every caller must state that this is an attempt to collect the debt by debt collector and any information obtained will be used for that purpose. Oh, we did speak with you, it looks like last week, but we were speaking with you about a Republic Finance account that you had set up with, not the other company.\nuser: Yeah, but I can't do that to the 13th. But he also said I had one with Citric Bank for $338. Am I got the wrong number?\nassistant: Yeah, that's\u2014 yes, you called the wrong number for that. I'm sorry.\nuser: Okay, well, I need to inform you that the bank told me a story. It's going to be the 14th, but I'm still going to pay it. But now I don't know what number I got to call for them because I thought that he told me to call this, this number.\nassistant: Oh yeah, I'm sorry, I apologize about that. I wouldn't be able to help you out with that one because we\u2014 that's a completely different company than us. I'm sorry, man.\nuser: Okay, well, just keep me on form.\nuser: As soon as I get the, the money for the, the, the The other one, I'll call you back, but I got to find the number to that other man, and I don't know, I thought it was through y'all.\nassistant: No, that's not us. I'm sorry, I apologize.\nuser: Okay, just, uh, I'll call you back on the 14th, 13th or the 14th, sir, whenever they turn it loose at the bank. I want to write this morning,\nassistant: Okay. Ah, this there. Thank you.\nuser: still won't turn it loose, but They got to turn it loose, but I don't know when. So just give me to the 13th and see if,\nassistant: Right.\nuser: uh, they\u2014 that I can\u2014 I'm a new customer and it's like a 14-day hold on it. So just as soon as I get it, sir, I'll give it to you.\nuser: Thank you.\nassistant: Okay. All right, give us a call on that time and we'll go from there. You're welcome.\n```\n\n# Response Format\nReturn ONLY the new contact info in JSON format.\n{\n  \"new_phone\": \"The new phone number provided by the user/customer, return null if not available\",\n  \"new_mail\": \"The new mailing address provided by the user/customer, return null if not available\",\n  \"new_email\": \"The new email address provided by the user/customer, return null if not available\"\n}\n\n# Examples\n- Customer says \"My new number is 555-1234\" \u2192 Extract \"555-1234\"\n- Customer says \"You can reach me at john@email.com\" \u2192 Extract \"john@email.com\"\n- Customer says \"I moved to 123 Main St, Apt 5B\" \u2192 Extract \"123 Main St, Apt 5B\"\n- Customer says \"My lawyer's number is...\" \u2192 Do NOT extract (not customer's info)\n- Agent says \"Our company number is...\" \u2192 Do NOT extract (company info, not customer's)"
