[2026-05-13 22:02:21 +0700] [CODEX] output/from_zero/main_yaml_v1_full/per_conversation/0076_TpPFkJnybFDlpReVAwb6oA/llm_call_0003.json:28:      "content": "# Objective\nYou are a reviewer agent in the finance and banking sector.\nYou will receive a transcript of a phone call related to debt collection and recovery, located in the section PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT.\nThe transcript includes two participants: the debt collector (assistant) and the customer (user).\nYour task is to analyze this transcript and write a write a short, concise, and simple summary of the call focusing on the customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n\n# PHONE_CALL_TRANSCRIPT\nassistant: Hello\nuser: Hello?\nassistant: Hello, I am Sarah, a virtual agent on a recorded line.\nassistant: May I please speak with Margaret Thornton?\nuser: This is she.\nassistant: Hi Margaret, to protect your privacy and consent to proceed with the call, could you please confirm your month and day of birth?\nuser: March nine nineteen seventy one.\nassistant: Got it.\nassistant: Just to confirm, you said March 9th.\nassistant: Is that correct?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Thanks.\nassistant: Again, my name is Sarah - a virtual assistant from Kompato.\nassistant: This is an attempt to collect a debt by a debt collector.\nassistant: Any information obtained will be used for that purpose.\nassistant: In case we're disconnected, may I call you back at this number?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Okay  For your convenience, is it okay if we communicate via text?\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Thank you.\nuser: I would\nassistant: Gotcha  Could you please share the circumstances that led to this balance?\nuser: I got sick, and I had leave my job.\nuser: I'm not on not able to work anymore. That's what happened.\nassistant: I'm sorry to hear about your situation, Margaret.\nassistant: That must have been a challenging time for you.\nassistant: Are you currently receiving any assistance, such as disability benefits or other support, to help with your financial situation?\nuser: No.\nassistant: I understand, Margaret.\nuser: Not at this time. I'm not. I put in for my Social Security disability. I just haven't heard anything back from you yet.\nassistant: I understand, Margaret.\nassistant: Waiting for Social Security disability can take time, and I hope you hear back soon with positive news.\nassistant: In the meantime, is there any other support or resources you\u2019re exploring to help with your situation?\nuser: No, ma'am. It isn't.\nassistant: Thank you for sharing, Margaret.\nassistant: Given your current situation, we can explore options that might work for you.\nassistant: How do you feel about starting with a small Keep in Touch payment of $25 per month for three months?\nassistant: This way, we can maintain communication and revisit the arrangement when your circumstances improve.\nuser: I have to I'll discuss and then see what I can do.\nassistant: Understood, Margaret.\nassistant: Would there be a good time over the next couple of weeks when we can follow up and discuss this further?\nassistant: This way, we can give you some time to consider your options.\nuser: We I got to go\nuser: the doctor tomorrow\nuser: and I got to see whether I will have surgery or not. So I will have to get back with you Call me back. Let me see what the day is. Thursday. Call me back next next Thursday.\nuser: And I can let you know something\nassistant: gotcha  Thank you for letting me know, Margaret.\nassistant: I\u2019ll arrange for a call back next Thursday to follow up with you.\nassistant: Before we end the call, let's make sure we have your correct contact information so you can receive important updates about your account in the future.\nassistant: Would you like to update your email, phone number, or mailing address?\nuser: I thought my email is\nassistant: I have margaretthornton at gmail dot com as your email address in my records.\nassistant: Is this still accurate?\nuser: How long? Let me see. If it's the right one.\nassistant: Sure, take your time.\nassistant: Is margaretthornton at gmail dot com still the correct email address for you?\nuser: It's marga thorns at three fifty at g mail dot com.\nassistant: Thank you for the update.\nassistant: Just to confirm, your email is margathorns350 at gmail dot com.\nassistant: Is that correct?\nuser: Rock. Yeah.\nassistant: Got it.\nassistant: Thank you, Margaret.\nassistant: I'll update your email to margathorns350 at gmail dot com.\nassistant: Now, I also have one zero three ELLIS Street SW, MILLEDGEVILLE, Georgia, three one zero six one as your mailing address in my records.\nassistant: Is this still accurate?\nuser: No, ma'am. It's all. Twelve o three O'Connor Street.\nuser: Milleyville, Georgia three one zero six one.\nassistant: Thank you for the update.\nassistant: Just to confirm, your new mailing address is 1203 O'Connor Street, Milledgeville, Georgia, 31061.\nassistant: Is that correct?\nuser: Right.\nuser: Yes.\nassistant: Thank you, Margaret.\nassistant: I've updated your mailing address to 1203 O'Connor Street, Milledgeville, Georgia, 31061.\nassistant: I'll follow up with you next Thursday as discussed.\nassistant: Take care, and I wish you the best with your doctor's appointment.\nuser: Alright. Thank you.\nassistant: You're welcome, Margaret.\n\n# Instructions\n1. Read the transcript carefully.\n2. Identify the key points and outcomes of the call focusing on customer's intent, key points, and outcomes.\n3. Write a short summary of the call, should ONLY 2-3 sentences\n4. Return the summary wrapped bettween <output> and </output> tags.\n\n# Example output format\n<output>\nYour summary here ...\n</output>"
