[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] ## Interpretation
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] The experiment confirms the wiring layer: transcript-backed rows can be turned into batch inputs, split by YAML, rerun on zero, and reconciled back to the source manifest. The useful signal is the mismatch ledger, not the aggregate accuracy alone. Those rows tell us where the current zero-shot call-code interpretation diverges from the source label.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] The candidate list is empty in this run, so exact top-1 agreement is the main metric for now. If the next pipeline version exposes a populated candidate set, this same report should start measuring whether the expected label is present below top-1.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] ## Next Experiment
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] Run **revive-01** on the 7 mismatches plus 7 matched controls from the same slice buckets.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] Hypothesis: if each mismatch is converted into a structured evidence card with decisive transcript span, expected label principle, predicted label principle, and disagreement class, then a seed builder can produce higher-quality zero-shot examples without weakening matched-anchor behavior.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] Procedure:
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Create one revive card per mismatch from the redacted debug audit and rerun ledger.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Add one matched control per affected slice bucket to detect overfitting.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Generate 1-2 candidate zero-shot seed examples per revive card.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Rerun only the 14-row revive set against the same YAML routes.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Accept the revive design only if mismatch recovery improves and matched controls do not regress.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] Gate: pass if at least 4 of 7 mismatches recover and 7 of 7 controls remain matched. Fail if any control regresses without a clear taxonomy issue.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
