[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] The human review CSV uses `transcript_version=redacted`. Names, phone numbers, emails, URLs, long numeric IDs, dates, and money amounts may be replaced with placeholders. This protects sensitive customer data, but it is not neutral for call-code definition work.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] When a code definition depends on exact identity, amount, date, contact, or legal-representation details, the raw transcript should be checked before accepting the classification decision.
