[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] ## Definition Impact
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] Redaction is lowest-risk for coarse outcomes such as pure hang-up/silence when only names are masked. It becomes definition-relevant when:
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] - identity verification depends on exact name, DOB, SSN, PIN, or account details;
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] - legal/compliance codes depend on who was named, what representation was claimed, or which contact channel was provided;
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] - payment/dispute codes depend on exact amount, due date, confirmation, or reference values;
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] - callback/transfer codes depend on exact time, contact number, or requested party.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] For the revive loop, use the redacted CSV for triage and the raw runner input only for rows flagged `raw_transcript_review_recommended=true` or any mismatch where the reviewer cannot decide from redacted evidence.
[2026-05-13 22:02:37 +0700] [CODEX] 
