[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - timestamp: 2026-05-13 10:25 UTC / 17:25 +07
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - author: claude (claude-opus-4-7)
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - inputs: `data/inputs/sanity_v2/master_30d_accounting_20260512.csv` (tenant), `per_conv_labels_30d_20260512_v5.csv` (dual labels + timestamps), `per_conv_30d_20260511_v4.csv` (diagnostic columns)
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - scripts: `scripts/affirm_callcode_flip_delta_20260513.py`, `scripts/affirm_flip_diagnose_20260513.py`
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - artifacts: `data/inputs/sanity_v2/affirm_flip_delta_{per_conv,summary,pairs,diagnostics}_20260513.csv`
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] ## TL;DR
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - 1,301 Affirm convs over the 30-day window. **545** have both a fast-classifier and a final-classifier `EndPostCallAnalysis`; 756 had only one (cannot flip).
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - Of paired Affirm convs: **consistent 79.82% (435) / flipped 20.18% (110)**. That's **~4× the global flip rate of 4.59%** — Affirm carries a tenant-specific flip risk.
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - Fast→final **delay** is much **shorter for flipped** convs: median **19,392 s (~5.4 h)** vs consistent **143,173 s (~39.8 h)**. The fast classifier fires while the final pipeline is still queued; convs that flip are the ones the final pass *rapidly* contradicted on a partial-transcript label.
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - Top flip pair is **HUP → NLM (29 convs, 26.4% of flips)** — every one was a rule-based HUP on a voicemail snippet that the LLM final pass relabeled as NLM (no live message).
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] - 3 mechanically distinct causes account for ≥85% of flips:
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX]   1. **Rule-based fast pass overridden by LLM final pass** — 30% (33/110). HUP→NLM dominates (29).
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX]   2. **YAML/policy drift mid-window** — 40% (44/110) had a *multi-hash* `ccd_hash` within a single conv. The dual-hash sub-cohort flips **39.7%** vs single-hash 11.4–23.7%.
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX]   3. **Sub-100-char transcript at fast time** — 38% (42/110). Mostly overlaps (1); the fast classifier had nothing substantive to work with.
[2026-05-13 22:02:43 +0700] [CODEX] 
