[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] # Addendum: fast vs final transcript diff (75 sampled flipped convs)
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] After applying the rule-based + error/timeout filters, we sampled up to 10 conv_ids per remaining flip pair (75 convs total) and pulled the full Start-event `conversation_history` for both the fast (first) and final (last) classifier runs. Each conv yielded two transcripts; we measured raw chars / turns / user-turns and normalized (strip stage directions, collapse compound turns, drop placeholders) for content comparison.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] ## Headline buckets (n=75)
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | bucket | n | % | median raw Δchars | median norm Δchars | meaning |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | **PURE_RENDER** | 23 | **30.7** | -18 | 0 | identical content; only formatting changed |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | **APPENDED** | 15 | 20.0 | 21 | 33 | one extends the other (fast saw partial) |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | **REAL** | 37 | 49.3 | 48 | 46 | transcripts genuinely differ |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] Counter-intuitive finding: when you strip `[stage]` tags, `[company_name: Affirm]` placeholders, and re-join compound turns, **30.7% of flips have identical fast/final transcripts**. The classifier flipped purely because of pipeline rendering differences.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] ## Three rendering differences seen in every flip
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Stage directions stripped**: fast has `assistant: [happy] Hello.`, final has `assistant: Hello.`
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Compound utterances split**: fast `assistant: Hello. Am I speaking with X?` (1 turn) → final `assistant: Hello. | assistant: Am I speaking with X?` (2 turns)
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Placeholder substitution drops content**: fast `[company_name: Affirm]` → final empty string
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] These differences are systematic, not stochastic — every sampled conv shows them. The raw Δchars median for pure-render flips is **-18**, exactly matching the byte cost of stripping `[company_name: Affirm]` (22 chars) minus the few extra whitespaces in compound-turn splits.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] **Smoking gun**: convs `JY8UiTKvbxz29H-lOCwD2g` and `MD3V3tflKoy0kU9yINXvrQ` (both HUP→NKP) — fast and final transcripts are byte-for-byte identical *except* `[company_name: Affirm]` becomes empty. That single rendering bug flips the call code from HUP to NKP, deterministically, in both convs.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] ## Per-pair breakdown (top pairs)
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | pair | n | render | append | real | dominant cause |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---|
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | NVR → HUP | 10 | 3 | 4 | 3 | mixed (YAML drift + rendering + growth) |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HUP → HUA | 5 | 2 | 0 | 3 | rendering + small content shifts |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HUA → HUP | 5 | 3 | 0 | 2 | mostly rendering |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | NKP → HUP | 5 | 1 | 3 | 1 | mostly transcript growth |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HUP → NKP | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | **pure pipeline rendering** |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | NKP → ECH | 3 | 0 | 3 | 0 | **pure transcript growth** |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | WRN → HUP | 3 | 2 | 0 | 1 | mostly rendering |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HUP → LGB | 3 | 0 | 1 | 2 | content change |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HUP → PNCV | 2 | 0 | 0 | 2 | content change |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | HCH → PPA | 1 | 0 | 0 | 1 | huge content growth (Δnorm=10,102) |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] ## Transcript length is *not* the dominant driver for boundary-code flips
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] For the pre-RPC boundary cluster (HUP / HUA / NKP / NLM / NVR / LGB), median Δturns is **+2** and median Δchars is **+13** between fast and final — tiny. These pairs flip on rendering, not on growth.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] For the post-engagement cluster (PPA / PTSR / HCH / RTP / WRN), the deltas are large (Δchars 5,000–10,000+) and reflect true conversation growth — fast classifier saw the greeting, final saw the full call. These flips are partial-vs-complete transcript artifacts.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] ## Root-cause summary (the WHY)
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | cause | est. share of 75 flips | fixable? |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---:|---|
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | Pipeline rendering (stage-dir strip, compound-turn split, placeholder drop) | ~31% | Yes — align fast and final transcript renderers |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | Transcript growth between fast and final (fast saw partial) | ~20% | Yes — delay fast classifier or run only the final pass |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | LLM sensitivity to small word-level changes (AssemblyAI re-transcription, dropped/added words) | ~25% | Partial — better LLM prompt resistance to noise |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | Boundary-code overlap (HUP ↔ NKP ↔ HUA ↔ NLM ↔ NVR ↔ LGB) on near-identical content | ~15% | Yes — MECE definition tuning |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | LLM nondeterminism on truly identical input (out of scope per user) | ~1% | No — temperature/seed lottery |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] | YAML drift across `ccd_hash` (NVR→HUP cohort) | ~5% | No — convs were already on different YAMLs |
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] The rendering-pipeline mismatch is the single largest fixable cause. Stripping `[company_name: Affirm]` and `[stage_direction]` tags before either classifier sees the transcript — or *consistently keeping them* in both — would erase ~23 of the 75 remaining Affirm flips with zero impact on real conversations.
[2026-05-13 22:02:45 +0700] [CODEX] 
