[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - each row has `conversation_history`, `dict_variable`, `raw_call_assignment`, `list_current_state`, and `label_v0`;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - YAML route is explicit;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - postprocess/system fixture rows are either excluded from prompt-only accuracy or reported separately.
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] Pass the rerun experiment only if:
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - global exact match is at least 90%, or all mismatches are explainable;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - `found_in` is higher than exact match for postprocess/priority mismatches;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - fixture rows are not counted as prompt failures;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] - flip-disagreement rows are routed to major-voter or human review instead of treated as high-confidence ground truth.
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] ## Important Distinction
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] The AGI-9466 runner creates conversations. The postcall rerun runner classifies conversations.
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] For OKR2, both are needed, but in this order:
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 1. production/signal selection;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 2. postcall rerun on a small CSV;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 3. mismatch analysis;
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 4. only then AGI-9466 synthetic top-up for coverage gaps.
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
