[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] # Signal Schema v0 - 2026-05-13
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] Purpose: test whether production conversations can be decomposed into evidence-backed `conversation_signal` rows before scaling the OKR2 dataset.
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] ## Required Fields
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | Field | Meaning |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `conversation_id` | Source conversation id from `source_pool_ledger_20260512.csv` |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `signal_id` | Stable id for one signal inside the conversation |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `slice` | Experiment route: high-trust, compliance, flip, below-floor, fixture |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `source_route` | Dataset route such as `prod_exact_current_yaml`, `flip_disagreement_audit`, or `postprocess_fixture` |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `local_yaml_match_paths` | Exact local YAML prompt+CCD match if available |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `primary_code` | Main code this signal evaluates |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `tree_path` | Root/trunk/leaf signal path |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `neighbor_codes` | Codes this signal should be distinguished from |
[2026-05-13 22:02:49 +0700] [CODEX] | `assistant_inquiry` | Redacted assistant utterance that frames the user response |
