[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ===== notetodo/2026-05-13-okr2-signal-dataset-plan.md =====
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] # OKR2 Signal Dataset Plan - 2026-05-13
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ## Decision
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Build the next dataset as a **signal-first source pool**, not as a larger AGI-9466 synthetic sweep.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] AGI-9466 remains useful, but only as a controlled generator for below-floor and boundary cases after production evidence is exhausted. The core dataset should be derived from production conversations, decomposed into evidence-backed signal paths, then promoted into balanced eval, production holdout, fixture, flip-audit, and synthetic-top-up artifacts.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ## Why this is the right move
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Yesterday's work already crossed the biggest accounting hurdle:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - `data/inputs/sanity_v2/source_pool_ledger_20260512.csv` accounts for all 47,153 production conversations.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - `docs/local_yaml_alignment_correction_20260512.md` shows 36,617 conversations match a current local prompt plus call-code-description pair, mostly `en_collin_kompato_payment_dtmf/main.yaml`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - `docs/source_pool_ledger_summary_20260512.md` separates eligible production rows, flip-disagreement rows, postprocess fixture rows, system-rule rows, no-action rows, and below-floor rare rows.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - `input/testset_main_yaml_v2_20260511_v4_dtmf_aligned.csv` already proves a 624-row DTMF-aligned balanced sample is possible.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] The remaining gap is not "more rows." The remaining gap is **signal structure**:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - A conversation can contain multiple relevant signals, while the final call code records only one winner.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Later intent can override earlier intent, but earlier high-value signals still matter for training, QA, and Auto-QC.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Compliance and legal signals must outrank reporting convenience.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Some codes are prompt/LLM-emitted; others are postprocess or system-rule outputs and need fixture tests.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - AGI-9466 zero-shot seeds produce clean target behavior, but they do not automatically cover production ambiguity, multi-signal turns, ASR noise, or postprocess behavior.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ## Brainstorming Pass
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ### Option A - Major voter first
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Run 3-5 strong LLMs over every transcript and ask a reviewer to choose final evidence and call codes.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Pros:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Fast conceptual path to multi-signal labels.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Good for difficult boundary rows and flip-disagreement rows.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Cons:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Too expensive and noisy for 47k row membership.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Lets LLMs define ground truth before deterministic accounting.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Can hide YAML/version drift and postprocess/system layers.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Use only after deterministic routing, for low-confidence rows, synthetic acceptance, and rerun mismatch triage.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ### Option B - AGI-9466 generation first
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Expand AC seeds and generate L1/L2 conversations until every code has enough examples.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Pros:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Directly attacks rare-code coverage.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - AC seed format is strong for explicit intent, must-say, must-not-say, and distinct-from boundaries.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Cons:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Repeats known AGI-9466 limits: structural HTT/ECH, warm-transfer mock gaps, priority rerank artifacts, score-4 quality cliff, and synthetic examples that are cleaner than production.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Does not solve production label confidence or Auto-QC.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Use after production rows are exhausted, with stricter acceptance gates.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] ### Option C - Production final label only
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Use `label_v0_last` as ground truth and sample to quotas.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Pros:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Deterministic and cheap.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Already close to usable for DTMF-aligned rows.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Cons:
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Throws away minor but important signals.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Treats first/final flips as ordinary labels instead of Auto-QC signal.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] - Cannot explain why two codes were reasonable in the same call.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] Use as the baseline label, not the final signal truth.
[2026-05-13 22:03:01 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ### Chosen option - Tree-signal hybrid
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Use production ledger rows as the source of truth for row existence and YAML lineage; then build a **signal tree per conversation** that records evidence spans and candidate codes. Use major voters only on low-confidence or high-value rows. Use AGI-9466 only to fill uncovered signal paths.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ## Signal Data Model
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] The dataset unit should be `conversation_signal`, not only `conversation`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Minimum fields:
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Field | Purpose |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `conversation_id` | Join back to source ledger and rerun packet |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `signal_id` | Stable per-conversation signal identifier |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `tenant_normalized` | Keep Kompato, inferred Kompato, Affirm, Mariner visible |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `local_yaml_match_path` | Exact YAML/prompt lineage for rerun |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `source_route` | `prod_exact`, `prod_historical`, `fixture`, `flip_audit`, `synthetic_ac_seed` |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `tree_path` | Root to trunk to leaf, e.g. `phone_holder/customer/payment_interest/partial_settlement` |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `call_code_candidates` | All defensible codes for this signal |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `primary_code` | The code this dataset row trains/evaluates |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `neighbor_codes` | Codes this row should distinguish from |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `evidence_turn_start` / `evidence_turn_end` | Span supporting the signal |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `assistant_inquiry` | The assistant question or prompt that made the user response meaningful |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `user_evidence` | Minimal user utterance evidence, not full transcript duplication |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `signal_explicitness` | `explicit`, `implicit_high_value`, `implicit_low_value` |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `signal_level` | L1 happy path, L2 confusing/cooperative, L3 adversarial/noisy |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `temporal_rank` | Later signal can override earlier signal |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `risk_priority` | compliance, legal, payment, transfer, ops, no-action |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `label_confidence` | high, medium, low, quarantine |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | `adjudication_source` | prod label, deterministic rule, major voter, human, AC reviewer |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] This preserves the user's tree idea: root determines who/what is on the phone, trunks represent major conversation phases, leaves represent specific outcomes or action codes.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ## Tree Skeleton
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Start with these top-level trunks and refine from real data:
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Phone contact state: `NKP`, `HUP`, `NLM`, `LM`, `ECH`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Identity and party relation: `IDV`, `IDF`, `WRN`, `TPC`, `HUA`, `NVR`, `RCR`, `LGB`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Compliance/legal protection: `DNC`, `CDS`, `WCR`, `ATY`, `BKP`, `DSA`, `CPR`, `FRA`, `DIS`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Engagement and willingness: `PPA`, `RTP`, `NNP`, `CAB`, `NCV`, `HCH`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Payment/settlement outcome: `PAY`, `PIF`, `SIF`, `PSIF`, `PPIF`, `FDP`, `DCP`, `TPM`.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 6. Transfer/human escalation: `TSR`, `TLM`, `EPT`, `HTT`, `FTP`, `WFR`, promise transfer variants.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 7. Administrative/special handling: `LGH`, `PRS`, `CSM`, and other rare operational codes.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Do not force these trunks to be mutually exclusive at conversation level. Enforce MECE at the sibling-decision level inside one trunk.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ## Small-Scale Hypothesis Test
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Use this plan as an experiment first, not as a full-scale build.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ### Hypothesis
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Signal-tree labeling will produce a more useful dataset than final-label-only sampling because it captures explicit high-value signals, neighbor boundaries, and label-risk cases that the single production call code hides.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ### Null hypothesis
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] The signal-tree layer does not add enough value over the existing production final label. If the small test cannot produce clearer evidence spans, better boundary labels, or useful Auto-QC queues, then scale-up should stop and the work should fall back to ordinary balanced sampling plus fixtures.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ### Experiment slice
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Build a 40-row experiment from already-accounted source rows:
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Slice | Rows | Purpose |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---:|---|
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | High-trust anchors | 10 | Sanity check that simple rows stay simple |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Compliance/legal | 10 | Test whether explicit high-risk signals are easy to span-label |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Flip-disagreement | 8 | Test whether first-vs-final mismatch is useful Auto-QC signal |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Below-floor real production | 6 | Test whether rare rows are usable before synthetic top-up |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] | Postprocess/system fixture | 6 | Test whether fixture routing stays separate from prompt eval |
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] Use exact current local YAML matches first, especially the `payment_dtmf/main.yaml` group. If a needed rare row is not available in exact-current YAML, mark it as `prod_historical_yaml_recovery` instead of silently mixing versions.
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] ### What to build
[2026-05-13 22:03:02 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] Create these experiment artifacts:
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - `docs/plan/signal_schema_v0_20260513.md`
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - `data/inputs/sanity_v2/signal_experiment_40_manifest_20260513.csv`
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - `data/inputs/sanity_v2/signal_experiment_40_annotations_20260513.jsonl`
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - `docs/signal_experiment_40_report_20260513.md`
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] Each annotated signal row must include:
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - assistant inquiry span;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - user evidence span;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - tree path;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - primary code;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - neighbor codes;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - explicitness level;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - temporal rank;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - risk priority;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - adjudication source;
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] - why final production label is sufficient or insufficient.
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] ### Measurements
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] The experiment passes only if it clears these gates:
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Metric | Pass gate |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---:|
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Source reconciliation | 40/40 rows join back to `source_pool_ledger_20260512.csv` |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Version/routing clarity | 40/40 rows have explicit source route and YAML/prompt/CCD status |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Evidence quality | >= 34/40 rows have a clear assistant/user evidence span |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Signal lift | >= 8/40 rows contain a useful secondary or higher-value signal not represented by final label alone |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Auto-QC lift | >= 50% of flip rows produce an actionable disagreement reason |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Fixture separation | 6/6 fixture rows are excluded from prompt-only eval |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] | Reviewer usability | 30-row spot review can validate the annotation without opening raw JSONL |
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] ### Experiment decision
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] After the 40-row test, choose one:
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Scale**: gates pass; implement `signal_pool_v0` for 150-300 rows.
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Revise**: signal schema is useful but evidence extraction is weak; tighten schema and rerun another 40-row test.
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Fallback**: signal layer does not add value; use final-label balanced sampling plus separate fixture and flip-audit sets.
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] No 750-row dataset build should start until this experiment passes.
[2026-05-13 22:03:03 +0700] [CODEX] 
