[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] ## Summary
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] Today’s work moved Q2 postcall evaluation from source accounting into runnable, reviewable experiment design. The main progress was proving a small signal-first evaluation loop, extending the reviewer-ensemble path for coverage growth, and tightening the boundary between shareable aggregate reporting and sensitive conversation evidence.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] ## Q2 OKR Alignment
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] | OKR | Today’s Progress | Reporting Value |
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|---|
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] | KR1: expand evidence-backed call-code coverage | Advanced both the signal-first experiment path and the reviewer-ensemble path, turning source-pool material into candidate evaluation rows with clear routing and quality gates. | Coverage growth can be reported as a governed pipeline, not as manually assembled examples. |
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] | KR2: reduce human-QC burden through Auto-QC | Converted disagreement, fast-vs-final instability, model-choice risk, and redaction impact into review-priority signals. | Human review can focus on rows where the system has a measurable reason to be uncertain. |
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] ## Work Captured From Today’s Recaps
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Signal-first experiment: completed a small end-to-end pilot from source selection through rerun, mismatch review, and transcript-first human review design.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Reviewer-ensemble pilot: validated a multi-reviewer labeling path for expanding under-covered call-code cases, including a correction that future runs should test model diversity instead of only prompt diversity.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Fast-vs-final stability analysis: separated label instability caused by added content, rendering differences, and model-choice assumptions, then paused the conclusion until it is checked against the production classifier model.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] ## Approach
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Start from accounted production-derived evidence before expanding the evaluation set.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Keep evaluation populations separate: high-confidence anchors, disagreement rows, compliance-sensitive rows, deterministic system rows, and rows that require human adjudication.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Require version and route alignment before using a row for current-quality reporting.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Treat reviewer disagreement as signal, not noise; use it to prioritize Auto-QC and seed-revival work.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Keep redaction visible in the review process so masked evidence is not over-interpreted when exact wording matters.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] ## Data Selection And Alignment
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Selection gate: choose rows because they test a specific signal, not just because they are available.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Required-input gate: only rerun rows whose conversation evidence and state inputs are complete enough for the target evaluation layer.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Configuration gate: do not mix current-route results with historical or mismatched configurations in the same headline metric.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Review gate: route disagreements, sensitive evidence masking, and fast-vs-final instability into human review before treating them as high-confidence labels.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] - Scale gate: expand only after the small experiment proves both the runner path and the human-review packet shape.
[2026-05-14 22:02:04 +0700] [CODEX] 
