[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] ### Within-day ticket ordering
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] Order STAR blocks so the **flagship contribution lands first**:
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Closures + milestones first** — anything that hit Done today, hit a metric, or shipped a deliverable.
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Active in-progress work next** — substantive contributions that aren't yet closed.
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **Sprint planning / scoping last** — tickets created today as scope buckets (e.g. DCI-321/322/328 created on Apr 22).
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **Admin / maintenance at the bottom** — status-only updates, ticket triage. Often these don't deserve a STAR block at all; collapse to a "DCI activity today" bullet list.
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] The Tickets table at the top should follow the same order, so the reviewer sees the headline first in both the table and the Detail section.
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] ### Credits boundary
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] Credits is a **due-recognition** section, not an attendance list. Apply this filter:
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] | Contribution type | Credit? |
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] |---|---|
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] | Defined a spec, shipped a fix, validated UAT, authored seeds, made a same-day decision that unblocked progress | ✅ Yes — name them with their specific contribution |
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] | Cc'd on a comment, watched the ticket, was the formal assignee but didn't act today | ❌ No |
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] | Story owner / Product Owner role-only mention with no action | ❌ No |
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] | Reviewed in passing, no specific feedback or change | ❌ No |
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] If after filtering nobody remains, **drop the entire `**Credits.**` line**. Don't pad with "Hai Trung — story owner" when story-owner role didn't make a move that day.
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] ### Links section — bulleted with descriptions
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] The reviewer can't open files on your laptop. Every linked artifact gets a **1-line description** explaining what it is and why it's referenced here. Example:
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] ```markdown
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] **Links.**
[2026-05-14 22:02:08 +0700] [CODEX] - `testing/inputs/testset_agi7771_v1.csv` — frozen 17-row golden testset (sha256 `d55a5796`) used by the AGI-7771 backtest.
