[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] ## Decision Governance
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] When facts conflict, apply this precedence order:
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 1. Latest Jira ticket status/comments/changelog for the active ticket.
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 2. Approved business/product decision recorded in the ticket thread.
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 3. Active config/spec references used by current execution.
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 4. Historical completed tickets (baseline knowledge).
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 5. Local notes/planners (supporting layer, not primary source of truth).
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] If new evidence contradicts prior understanding, update the decision register and impacted ticket notes in the same sync cycle.
[2026-05-14 22:03:16 +0700] [CODEX] [2026-05-14 22:02:09 +0700] [CODEX] 
