[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] ## Blockers / open questions
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] - **Gemini-3-flash rerun outstanding.** The headline 96% PURE_RENDER agreement was measured on `gpt-5.5`; production uses `gemini-3-flash`. Local LLM Hub key (`.env.llmhub` → `llmhub.tsengineering.io`) only allows `openai/gpt-5.5` and `openai/gpt-5.3-codex`. To unblock: either SSH to `192.168.5.250` and run the script there with zero's broader key, or get the local key extended. User input needed to pick path.
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] - **LGB definition has a clean miss.** Conv `vToIkPujyyHOi0VRkfvrew` — bot says verbatim "I understand that you want to speak in another language other than English" in both fast and final transcripts, yet classifier predicted HUP (raw) and NVR (redacted). The yaml's LGB description should match the bot's own language-barrier acknowledgement pattern. Few-shot tweak independent of redaction.
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] - **`[company_name: Affirm]` placeholder rendering bug.** Final-pass transcript renderer substitutes the placeholder to an empty string instead of the actual company name. Two HUP→NKP convs (`JY8UiTKvbxz29H-lOCwD2g`, `MD3V3tflKoy0kU9yINXvrQ`) are byte-identical except for this difference and both flipped. Pipeline-engineer ticket worth filing.
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] - **PURE_RENDER bucket has n=23**, wide confidence interval on the 96%/4% split. Plausible true rate anywhere from ~0% to ~20% with this sample. If the gemini-3-flash rerun returns a similar number, worth expanding the bucket by pulling more byte-identical pairs from the broader 5k-conv multi-hash cohort to tighten the CI.
[2026-05-14 22:03:18 +0700] [CODEX] - **PII redaction (R2) not yet tested.** Names appear in 55% of flipped Affirm convs; phone digits in 8%. Effect of masking these on the dominant flip pairs (HUP/HUA/NKP/NLM/NVR/LGB) is untested. R1 robustness suggests R2 would also have small effect, but worth running a small follow-up (~$1-2, ~10 min) if PII-policy pressure arrives.
