[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] - KR1 sample-DB seed is delivered: **675 (assistant_Q, user_A) canonical exemplars across 45 codes × 3 levels × 5 each** at `output/exemplars_v2_20260514_0916/canonical_exemplars.csv`, uploaded to the team Sheet as tab `1c_intents_v2`. Cost: $1.88 total for all of today's LLM work.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] - Two failed-experiment cycles preceded the win: (a) voter ensemble (yesterday) was misaligned to KR1's evidence-locator primitive, (b) Phase 1B real-conv extractor with rule-laden prompt hit only 35-50% agreement against the user's hand-graded 14-row calibration set. Both got abandoned.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] - The winning approach inverts the task: instead of extracting evidence from messy real conversations, generate canonical exemplars from scratch with a light-weight LLM, anchored to a bot question repertoire + tight per-code L1 disambiguation rules.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] - One sentence the user gave that decided the pivot: *"the rule-based detection is not going to work well. unless the user always said 'Do not call' for DNC, use LLM, maybe light weight one to create evidence of that call code for that level."*
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ## What was tried (hypothesis → experiment → result → reflect)
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ### Cycle 1 — Audit yesterday's voter Phase 1 (review-CSV + viewer)
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Hypothesis**: Yesterday's voter ensemble output (`testset_review_postprocessed.csv`, 160 rows) is review-ready for KR1, provided the schema is reshaped to fit `CsvReview_v2.html`'s dialect and Google Sheets co-edit workflow.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Experiment**: Aligned `build_testset_rows.py` output schema to §7.5 of the runbook (column-order chunking by 5-8 cognitive chunks; `reviewer_notes` next to evidence; voter dialect badges in viewer). Re-rendered 160 rows.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Result**: CSV opens cleanly in `CsvReview_v2.html` with the new voters-dialect badges (level / reviewer_verdict / agreement). Distributions: 56 strict / 60 miss / 44 defensible.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Reflect**: The schema work was useful plumbing, but the user's question — *"what is the next step on Phase 2?"* — surfaced a deeper problem: the voter ensemble is a classifier-verifier (KR2 territory), not the evidence-locator that KR1 needs. Voter outputs *happen* to include evidence_turns, but the primitive is wrong. Quotation captured in [`20260514_reflection_may13_planning_docs.md`](../thinking/20260514_reflection_may13_planning_docs.md).
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ### Cycle 2 — Phase 1B intent extractor (real-conv mining)
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Hypothesis**: Treating `(conv_id, target_code)` as input where `target_code ∈ prod.list_call_codes`, a single LLM call per pair can locate user-utterance evidence + tag L1/L2/L3 + emit 4-axis confidence (lexical / position / phase-alignment / discriminative power). 149 rows, all 45 codes, ~$5 budget.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Experiment**: Built `src/intent_extract/{prompt,sampler,runner,build_csv,postprocess_map}.py`. Sampler stratified by target code from `master_30d_accounting_20260512.csv` + `per_conv_30d_20260511_v3.csv`, filtered to Kompato + newer-policy hash. Runner: async per-row LLM calls via LLM Hub, `gpt-4o`, concurrency=5.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Result**: 149 rows, $3.82, 93% `evidence_found=true`, distribution L1: 75% / L2: 23% / L3: 1%. Quality on quick inspection looked solid. Notable finding (validated yesterday's voter spot-check): the 5 prod-emitted `INC` rows in this sample are actually `DEC` cases — the extractor refused to anchor INC to "she died" utterances, with explicit notes.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Reflect**: Output looked good but a deeper review against the user's hand-grading exposed systematic issues — load-bearing rules in the prompt were ignored. Details in next cycle.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ### Cycle 3 — L1 calibration against 14 user-annotated rows
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Hypothesis**: A v2 prompt with tighter L1 (single substantive intent; pair-in-isolation litmus) + a `better_fit_code` field + code-specific disambiguation (ATY/BKP/NNP/CAB/DNC/TPC) achieves ≥80% agreement with the user's hand-grading on the 17-row calibration subset.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Experiment**: User reviewed 17 rows in Google Sheets ([`intent_review` tab](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jwTsoz3jRuZ3AyxlDN9OgwHMw4v-6F91X8G27Ez5kTc/edit?gid=1480612147)) and wrote `reviewer_notes` on 14. Rewrote prompt to v2; re-ran extractor on same 17 rows.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Result**: **Only 6 of 17 clearly agreed (35%); 4 partial; 7 clearly disagreed.** Four recurring failure modes:
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 1. *Q-mark and single-word rules ignored* when broader transcript eventually resolves intent (the model reads past the evidence pair).
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 2. *"Information value" rule too rigid* on ATY ↔ BKP boundary — user's actual heuristic is "what is the user asking us to act on", not "which signal is named first".
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 3. *better_fit_code* restricted to prod-emitted codes, so multi-turn DNC-from-CDS case couldn't flag DNC.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 4. *Multi-turn evidence pattern* not detected (TPC + PCAB packed into "Five." answering "When's a good callback time?").
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Reflect**: Stacking explicit rules into a single prompt fails when the LLM has to apply 4-5 rules simultaneously in one inference. Rule-following is unreliable in single-shot — the model defaults to plausible-sounding judgement instead of strict rule application. **Real-conv extraction with abstract rules is a dead end.**
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ### Cycle 4 — Pivot to synthetic generation (Phase 1C)
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Hypothesis** (user-prompted): Generating canonical (Q, A) exemplars per (code, level) with a light-weight LLM is cheaper, more controllable, and dodges the rule-application problem — the LLM only needs to *produce* clean exemplars, not *detect* their cleanliness in messy real text.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Experiment**: Built `src/intent_extract/generate_exemplars.py`. One LLM call per code generates 5 exemplars × 3 levels = 15 exemplars. Smoke on 5 codes (ATY, BKP, DNC, CAB, DSA) with `gpt-4o-mini`. Output schema: `code, level, exemplar_idx, evidence_qa_pair, assistant_question_verbatim, user_response_verbatim, rationale, lexical_evidence_match, information_value, stylistic_notes, reviewer_notes`.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Result**: 75 exemplars, $0.01, ~60s wall. Quality strong on visual inspection — BKP L1 had chapter + case number; CAB L1 had explicit time; ATY L1 had attorney mention with name; DNC L1 was clean stop-call; DSA L1 named a debt-relief company. Scaled to full 45 codes (1 parse error on DSA, retried with `gpt-4o`): 675 exemplars total, $0.13, ~4.5 min. Uploaded to Sheet tab [`1c_intents`](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jwTsoz3jRuZ3AyxlDN9OgwHMw4v-6F91X8G27Ez5kTc/edit?gid=763087654).
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Reflect**: Synthetic generation is the right primitive for KR1 sample-DB seed. The simulator team can lift any (code, level) exemplar directly. **Cost ratio vs Phase 1B**: $0.13 vs $3.82 for inferior output. The rule-application problem dissolves because the LLM is producing, not detecting.
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] ### Cycle 5 — L1 single-intent refinement (Phase 1C v2)
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:19 +0700] [CODEX] **Hypothesis** (after user review): L1 currently has multi-intent contamination (the user pointed to `"I'm their sister, you can call back after 6 PM"` as a TPC + PCAB pack). Refining the prompt with (a) the single-substantive-intent rule, (b) concrete TPC/BKP/ATY/CAB/DNC counter-examples, (c) the 4-stage bot question repertoire (so assistant Qs are authentic), and (d) upgrading to `gpt-4o` for stricter rule-following, will produce clean single-intent L1.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] **Experiment**: Saved `feedback_L1_single_intent.md` to memory. Rewrote prompt with code-specific disambiguation rules. Smoked on 5 codes (TPC, DNC, ATY, BKP, CAB) with `gpt-4o-mini` — TPC L1 still contaminated. Switched to `gpt-4o` and ran full 45-code regeneration.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] **Result**: 675 exemplars, $1.75, ~87s wall, 0 parse errors. L1 quality dramatically cleaner:
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - TPC L1: third-party identification + alternative contact (different number / location), no callback-time contamination.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - BKP L1: all past-tense filed + Chapter or case number.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - ATY L1: all present-tense attorney references.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - CAB L1: all explicit date + time.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - DNC L1: clean single-intent stop-call.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - WCR L1: correctly combines stop-calling + alternate-channel preference (which IS WCR's definition).
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] Uploaded to Sheet tab [`1c_intents_v2`](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jwTsoz3jRuZ3AyxlDN9OgwHMw4v-6F91X8G27Ez5kTc/edit?gid=659663005).
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] **Reflect**: Two things landed the win: (1) **model-strength matters more than prompt cleverness** — `gpt-4o-mini` failed at TPC even with explicit counter-examples; `gpt-4o` got it on the first try; (2) **concrete counter-examples beat abstract rules** — the prompt now says `L1 BAD: "This is his sister, call back after 5 PM."` next to `L1 GOOD: "This is his sister. You can reach him at his work, 555-1234."` rather than just stating the single-intent principle.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] ## What was decided
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **KR1 sample-DB seed = synthetic canonical exemplars, NOT real-conv mining.** The voter ensemble (yesterday) and Phase 1B real-conv extractor (today) are both archived as KR2 / Auto-QC tooling, not the KR1 deliverable.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **L1 definition** locked: single substantive intent; trivial filler OK; second substantive code-signal disqualifies. Captured in `feedback_L1_single_intent.md` memory with the TPC/PCAB counter-example.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **Bot question repertoire** is scoped to 4 inquiry stages (IDV, open situation post-Mini-Miranda, negotiation waterfall, callback/exception). Synthetic exemplar generator must draw assistant Qs from these — no invented probing questions.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **Code-specific L1 disambiguation rules** live in the prompt (not in code), explicit counter-examples per code:
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX]   - TPC: third-party ID + new contact (not callback timing)
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX]   - BKP: past-tense + chapter / case-number (no future intent)
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX]   - ATY: present-tense (no future intent)
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX]   - CAB: explicit date + time (no vague timing, no Q-marks)
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX]   - DNC: broad stop-call (combining with email/mail → that's WCR)
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **Model choice**: `gpt-4o` for the final canonical-exemplar generation (not `gpt-4o-mini`) — rule-following strength matters at the discriminative boundaries. Cost penalty is trivial ($1.75 vs $0.13 for 675 rows).
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] - **Voters work**: archived, **not deleted**. The Phase 1 voter-ensemble outputs in `output/voters_pilot_20260513_0847_phase1/` stay on disk as the KR2 (Auto-QC) baseline.
[2026-05-14 22:03:20 +0700] [CODEX] 
