[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] ## What was decided
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] - **KR1 sample-DB seed = synthetic canonical exemplars, NOT real-conv mining.** The voter ensemble (yesterday) and Phase 1B real-conv extractor (today) are both archived as KR2 / Auto-QC tooling, not the KR1 deliverable.
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] - **L1 definition** locked: single substantive intent; trivial filler OK; second substantive code-signal disqualifies. Captured in `feedback_L1_single_intent.md` memory with the TPC/PCAB counter-example.
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] - **Bot question repertoire** is scoped to 4 inquiry stages (IDV, open situation post-Mini-Miranda, negotiation waterfall, callback/exception). Synthetic exemplar generator must draw assistant Qs from these — no invented probing questions.
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] - **Code-specific L1 disambiguation rules** live in the prompt (not in code), explicit counter-examples per code:
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX]   - TPC: third-party ID + new contact (not callback timing)
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX]   - BKP: past-tense + chapter / case-number (no future intent)
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX]   - ATY: present-tense (no future intent)
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX]   - CAB: explicit date + time (no vague timing, no Q-marks)
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX]   - DNC: broad stop-call (combining with email/mail → that's WCR)
[2026-05-14 22:03:24 +0700] [CODEX] - **Model choice**: `gpt-4o` for the final canonical-exemplar generation (not `gpt-4o-mini`) — rule-following strength matters at the discriminative boundaries. Cost penalty is trivial ($1.75 vs $0.13 for 675 rows).
