[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] ## Durable insights
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] *TODO: consider promoting to memory or skill*
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 1. **Rule-following in single-shot LLM prompts is unreliable.** Phase 1B's calibration showed `gpt-4o` ignoring an explicit "Q-marks disqualify L1" rule when the broader transcript eventually resolved the intent. Stacking 4-5 rules in one prompt makes the model default to plausible-judgement mode instead of strict rule application. **Mitigations**: (a) use stronger models for rule-heavy tasks (`gpt-4o` over `gpt-4o-mini`), (b) replace abstract rules with concrete L1 GOOD / L1 BAD counter-examples, (c) split the task so each LLM call applies ≤2 rules.
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 2. **Generate-then-judge inverts the rule problem.** When the LLM has to *detect* a property (like single-intent) in messy real text, it fails. When the LLM has to *produce* text with that property, it succeeds. The synthetic exemplar generator is dramatically more reliable than the real-conv extractor with the same rules. **Generalizable pattern**: for "find X in messy data" tasks, consider whether "produce N examples of X" is the right inverted primitive.
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 3. **The bot's question repertoire is much narrower than I imagined.** AI debt-collector bots only ask 4 categories: IDV / open-situation / negotiation-waterfall / callback-exception. Most call codes fire on user-VOLUNTEERED signals to the open-situation Q, not as direct answers to probing questions. My initial Phase 1C v1 invented bot questions per code (e.g., *"Have you retained an attorney?"*) — these are inauthentic. Constraining synthetic Qs to the 4 real stages produced exemplars that match prod's bot behaviour.
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 4. **TPC and PCAB are deeply tangled in user speech.** *"I'm his sister, call back at 6 PM"* fires both. The clean disambiguation: TPC = third-party identification + ALTERNATIVE CONTACT (different phone / email / location). PCAB = callback timing on the CURRENT number. The single utterance often blurs them; L1 requires picking one and stripping the other. Worth capturing as a code-pair memory if this comes up again across pipelines.
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 5. **`gpt-4o-mini` is a great workhorse for high-volume cheap generation but breaks at discriminative boundaries.** Phase 1C v1 ($0.13, 675 rows) had reasonable L1 quality but consistent TPC + PCAB contamination. Phase 1C v2 ($1.75, same 675 rows) on `gpt-4o` cleared the contamination. **Rule of thumb**: cheap model for raw generation; flagship model when you need strict adherence to a small rule-set. The 13× cost increase was worth it.
[2026-05-14 22:03:25 +0700] [CODEX] 
