[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] +## Major Milestones
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX]  
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| OKR | Today's Progress | Reporting Value |
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -|---|---|---|
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| KR1: increase call-code test data size to >=750 and >=10 per call code | Advanced the sample database path with a controlled exemplar-generation method that covers the current call-code taxonomy across difficulty levels and is ready for team review. | Coverage growth can now proceed from a repeatable seed set instead of ad hoc examples or unreliable extraction from messy conversations. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| KR2: reduce human-QC bug reports through Auto-QC | Turned fast-vs-final instability, reviewer disagreement, and model-alignment risk into explicit review gates. | Human review can focus on cases where the system has a measurable reason to be uncertain, rather than rechecking every row manually. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] +- No new PR opened, review-ready PR, merge to `dev`/`main`, or shipped Jira milestone was found in my Jira contribution sweep after the 17:21 baseline snapshot.
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] +- Completed a post-baseline Affirm distribution-shift view that compares first-pass and master-code movement across adjacent day pairs.
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] +- The new view covers 115 code-pair rows across 6 day-to-day comparisons and 32 call codes, with 10 movements at or above a 10 percentage-point absolute change.
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] +- The biggest follow-up signal is HUP on May 10 to May 11, where the first-pass/master distribution moved by +51.48 percentage points. Treat this as a candidate regression or data-mix checkpoint, not a final product-quality claim.
