[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1: voter-review path | Reused the multi-reviewer call-code outputs as a candidate source for the KR1 sample database. | The review surface worked, but the primitive was wrong for KR1: it verifies and critiques labels rather than reliably producing clean per-code training examples. | Keep it as a KR2 Auto-QC and disagreement-detection baseline, not as the KR1 seed source. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1B: real-conversation extractor | Asked an LLM to inspect real conversations, locate the evidence for a target code, and assign difficulty level and confidence. | The first pass looked promising, but human calibration showed unstable rule-following at the exact boundaries KR1 needs. The model often read beyond the intended evidence pair and chose plausible judgements instead of strict labels. | Do not scale this as the main KR1 path. Archive it as a future augmentation path after better calibration. |
