[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1C: synthetic canonical generation | Inverted the task: generate clean examples for each code and difficulty level instead of extracting them from messy conversations. | Much cheaper and more controllable. It produced broad taxonomy coverage quickly, but the first version still mixed multiple intents in some easy examples. | Accept the direction, but add stricter single-intent constraints and review gates. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:35 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1C v2: tightened canonical generation | Regenerated with stronger boundary examples, authentic bot-question patterns, and a stronger model for rule adherence. | Easy-level quality improved materially on the reviewed boundary families. The output is now good enough to seed simulator review, while medium and hard levels still need spot-checking. | Use this as the current KR1 seed, with review and selective regeneration before treating it as final coverage. |
