[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] +> ### What I did
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] +> Built a compact distribution-shift summary for Affirm first-pass versus master-code analysis after the baseline snapshot. The output reduces the day-to-day comparison into a shortlist of large percentage-point movements, making it easier to decide which shifts deserve a deeper regression or data-mix check.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX]  
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- Selection gate: include examples because they cover a target code and difficulty level, not because they are easy to find.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- L1 gate: require one substantive intent; rows that combine multiple code signals should be reviewed or regenerated.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- Coverage gate: keep the seed set tied to the current call-code taxonomy and the quarter target for per-code balance.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- Production-record gate: use final stabilized labels for reporting; keep preliminary labels as diagnostic inputs.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- Model-alignment gate: do not publish rendering or redaction conclusions until checked against the production classifier setup.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] -- Review gate: treat voter disagreement and instability as routing signals for Auto-QC, not as failures to hide.
[2026-05-14 22:05:36 +0700] [CODEX] +**Result.**
