[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -Today's work moved Q2 postcall evaluation from analysis into governed sample generation and stability decisioning. The main contribution was an experiment ladder for the KR1 sample database: start with voter outputs, test real-conversation extraction, calibrate against human judgement, then pivot to controlled canonical-example generation when the earlier paths did not meet the bar. In parallel, the fast-vs-final classifier work was reframed as a quality-gate problem rather than a headline accuracy claim.
