[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -|---|---|---|
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| KR1: increase call-code test data size to >=750 and >=10 per call code | Advanced the sample database path with a controlled exemplar-generation method that covers the current call-code taxonomy across difficulty levels and is ready for team review. | Coverage growth can now proceed from a repeatable seed set instead of ad hoc examples or unreliable extraction from messy conversations. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| KR2: reduce human-QC bug reports through Auto-QC | Turned fast-vs-final instability, reviewer disagreement, and model-alignment risk into explicit review gates. | Human review can focus on cases where the system has a measurable reason to be uncertain, rather than rechecking every row manually. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] +- No new PR opened, review-ready PR, merge to `dev`/`main`, or shipped Jira milestone was found in my Jira contribution sweep after the 17:21 baseline snapshot.
