[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Trial | What We Tried | Outcome | Decision |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] +| # | Ticket | Status | Headline |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX]  |---|---|---|---|
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1: voter-review path | Reused the multi-reviewer call-code outputs as a candidate source for the KR1 sample database. | The review surface worked, but the primitive was wrong for KR1: it verifies and critiques labels rather than reliably producing clean per-code training examples. | Keep it as a KR2 Auto-QC and disagreement-detection baseline, not as the KR1 seed source. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1B: real-conversation extractor | Asked an LLM to inspect real conversations, locate the evidence for a target code, and assign difficulty level and confidence. | The first pass looked promising, but human calibration showed unstable rule-following at the exact boundaries KR1 needs. The model often read beyond the intended evidence pair and chose plausible judgements instead of strict labels. | Do not scale this as the main KR1 path. Archive it as a future augmentation path after better calibration. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1B calibration retry | Tightened the prompt with single-intent rules, better-fit-code logic, and code-specific disambiguation. | Agreement stayed below the target. Failure modes repeated around single-word answers, question-mark handling, multi-turn evidence, and adjacent code boundaries. | Treat real-conversation extraction with broad abstract rules as too brittle for the first seed. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1C: synthetic canonical generation | Inverted the task: generate clean examples for each code and difficulty level instead of extracting them from messy conversations. | Much cheaper and more controllable. It produced broad taxonomy coverage quickly, but the first version still mixed multiple intents in some easy examples. | Accept the direction, but add stricter single-intent constraints and review gates. |
[2026-05-14 22:05:52 +0700] [CODEX] -| Phase 1C v2: tightened canonical generation | Regenerated with stronger boundary examples, authentic bot-question patterns, and a stronger model for rule adherence. | Easy-level quality improved materially on the reviewed boundary families. The output is now good enough to seed simulator review, while medium and hard levels still need spot-checking. | Use this as the current KR1 seed, with review and selective regeneration before treating it as final coverage. |
